\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid11162986 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What is your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Full names is it? Roderick Llewellyn Lewis, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well now this is 6 Plas Treoda. Yes, Whitchurch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 And you are married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 The year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh wait a minute - when I was - thirty-three I think. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 The year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 1891 isn't it, that's 1891, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Here in Whitchurch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well I was ten when we moved - we moved from the Ph
ilogg up here onto the Common you see, I was ten then, it was about 1900 roughly, 1900 - 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 And you moved then onto the Common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Onto the Common. Plas Treoda, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How long did you live there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well right up until I got married and then I came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So you're still in Plas Treoda?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's right, I've been in Plas Treoda all my life, since I was about ten.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you know why the family moved from the Philog up to Plas Treoda?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well we wanted a little big
ger house, that's it. Yes, yes, get - my father was a builder you see and he built a house to suit the family then, and we had eight children, and we had an aunt living with us at the time, an old aunt from Somerset, my mother's - but she didn't last - sh
e didn't live much longer after we got there, but we wanted all the bed - all the bedrooms and things like that you see, that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well how - how do you want it, well I had three - three brothers and four sisters that way. That's what you went, yes, yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well - yes, you're - 1891, I was born 1891 - and - and what would he be then - what age did we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 We worked out he was thirty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Thirty-six when I was born wasn't it, that was you said, yes, I think so, I haven't got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - he was from - well the other side I remember him living was Pont Bach, Pont Bach Road, you know the old cottage, well it's
 all been done up now, but it's like on the - Back - Pont Bach Road there. So - yes, yes, it's all altered now, it was an old thatch cottage in our days you know. He was born there. He lived for a while in Cardiff, I think he got lodgings for a while and 
then he came back and built the house on the Philog and lived there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But he was actually born in Whitchurch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 He was actually born in Whitchurch really, yes, yes, oh he's Whitchurch, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 A builder, a - a carpenter and builder say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did he ever have an other job before he became a builder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. Oh he - well carpentry you see, he was in the trade you see, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 He started off as a carpenter?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's right, yes, what they do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Then he became a builder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What sort of building was he in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh house building, it's all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 In his own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, one man business like a - one business he was always in. That was the thing you see. There we
re two or three of them about in those days. There was Evans the builder we used to know one - one up the top you see, and there was Lewis the builder and all that see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would he actually build houses then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, he built those four we lived on
 ourselves and there were four cottages there. Of course he built Beechwood, that's where we lived and the next pair there, and built this - these blocks in College Road, the red bricked houses you know, was about - I don't know, the last three are with u
s
 now, my sisters got - one of those actually. Three - how many would there be, over a dozen houses - two - there are - long - long row of - red bricked - cottages there you see, he built all those. Now we just - well in fact those are the last built. Oh o
f
 course he built these houses here - couple of pairs of houses from the corner you know where the - the corner of Mer - Merthyr Road, yes, from Merthyr Road on. All those pairs there. He built those. That was just before 1901 because he were - they were q
u
ite new and I - but I - I never knew a time when they weren't there you see. But then he built - he built in town, in Corbridge Road. Corbridge Cottages, and - of course he had another habit of buying up old property and doing it up. Proper old - oh yes, 
in those days you could buy old stuff more or less for nothing you see, and - and then - doing them up you see, rebuilding practically you see. He had two or three bits with some old property like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Cardiff was expanding then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well that was t
he thing, Cardiff was expanding, 'cos that was - it was expanding and he built and he had but - he had a bit of job in getting rid of the houses, the ones in Coppice Road - at first you see. Things went quiet. But those houses - but after they came on ver
y well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I notice the houses along here have got the date on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, the date on, yes, on one or two of them, that's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 1898 I think is on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's right, be - they were building - complete just - before I - well, when I 
was - I was too young to know what was going on you see. Just about then. But I don't remember anything building built those, be Beechwood and the next two - this side of Beechwood, but - it's a block too there, and there were the four - four houses on th
e Philog. Our house with a - an archway under it there, old house. Well we lived in that house with the archway, because you see it gave them two extra bedrooms, so we weren't too badly off - for that then you see 'cos -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did he ever do any casual or part time work as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well wouldn't builder all his own time like you see. 'Cos he worked as a carpenter, what I - what - he went as - he was a carpenter and he started building you see, and then went back carpentering because build - business was a 
bit slow you see, building houses, you couldn't get rid of them or - things like that you see then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But nothing other than in the building trade really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would he employ people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. Yes, always getting - workmen. Painter
s and carpenters and - had great fun with some of them. There was one was an old - labouring chap from - an Irishman he was Old Jack we knew him as we kids, used to have great fun with him. Oh yes, yes, with the tradesmen you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When you say you'd have great fun with him, in what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well, when they were building those houses and they had him there I remember - he - he was a joker with us kids you see, pull our legs about things and tell us all kind of funny things you see. That's all. When he
 was working we were running around you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's lovely when there's building going on isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh for the children, oh we had a marvellous time you see, playing around with the stuff and all that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your father ever do any other job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. No, no, just the building and contractor like, builder and - carpenter and builder he called himself you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. Well things were slack at times I suppose but I knew nothing 
about it, I - that way you see. He was very well established by the time I knew - in fact what his - he was keen on - council work. Oh yes, he was on the - he was on the - School Board here, he was on the Parish Council and - they were all started in his 
t
ime you see, and he got on them - right from the start because a builder in a small - small village - was somebody. He was known by - he knew everybody and everybody knew him, a bit of business you see. He was somebody in a village you see in those days. 
A
nd - soon as any council he was on it and he kept right on 'til - he got on District Council finally the last - about ten years. And well he - he got on two or three schools, he was like the School Board originally I remember when that finished, the Schoo
l
 Board, you see and it turned on about 1911 I think and the - but the County took over the education you see. Well anyway on the Board of Guardians - what do you call it, the governors of the school see. No man - was it managers I - they call themselves, 
t
he Caerphilly Group - a group from Caerphilly see - well before - before we got into Cardiff it was the Caerphilly group we consisted of here, and then he was on the group for Llanduff, you see, as well, used to in the Llanduff schools, and old Vicar Butl
e
y, he was great pals with Old Vicar Butley he said, and - and Carephilly - group, and the Penarth County school. 'cos they were all like connected through the parish council then you see. But he was on those three lots. And he - he - he was great - he was
 strong on it you see, that was his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 He had great experience too didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well he was - if wanted - oh yes, he was very useful then on those councils you see for - for managing the buildings you see and repairs - and in fact he had - the - the
 First Grove school, and - Llanduff North - Hawthorn Road school there and Glenan school, they were built while he was on the - onto the board, and if you'll notice there's a little similar in style, the same architect, it was Rosslyn Williams of Cardiff 
-
 not Sandy Williams - oh dear - hm - oh yes, they're all within a few - you see the dates are on them actually you see - this - I could - they were built just before my time, just before 1891, or about 91 before I was old to enough - know anything about t
hem. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was a very interesting time here I should think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, we're coming - oh yes, yes, quite. Yes. Yes, 'cos -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 And your father was right on in it you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 He was - oh yes, he was - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well you can work that out now, how old - yes, from -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well she came from - Cummidge, near Bridgwater, in Somerset. Cummidge village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Had she any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, she
 was teaching, she was a - a mistress in - in the village school here then you see. She came over here at the age of fifteen - to start teaching. Yes, fifteen, yes I know. She was very small, she was quite - rather small person you know. I often wondered 
a
bout it really but in those days you see there was nothing doing down in Somerset so much - her sisters they were teachers down there you see in a little village in Somerset. Cummidge is a very small - actually I've never been there. I've been at Bridgwat
e
r but I've never been to Cummidge. It was a small place, you go - you've got to go to Bridgewater, just go out to it and come back, there's no through road, it's right out of the way, right out - out of the way so you never go there - or pass through in t
he ordinary way you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So she was a teacher before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did she work after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, no, no, not in those days. Not - not outside the home, she was probably busy with four - eight children, she worked all
 right but - or nine, ten you see, nine. Eight or nine, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Can you remember how many rooms there were in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 In Beechwood? Oh I can count up, let me see, I can count those up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Perhaps you could say them as you go in through the door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, yes - of course we change - we change their function later on but as they were - went on you see, front room was like a parlour in those days, just a drawing room. And then we had - there was a sitting room. On the other side
 there was a dining room which was a large room you see, and a large kitchen behind that, then there was a scullery, oh - and - and the pantry and lavatory, downstairs was a coal - a little coal house at the - but that was put - joined on at the back that
 was. That's the downstairs. And upstairs there was - there was one large bedroom and there were two smaller - two - still double bedrooms you see, double bedrooms. One single room - that faced on to a little balcony there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So there were three bedrooms?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh there - then - no, then there was - two or - three more bedrooms. One double bed and two single bedrooms. And bathroom and lavatory.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How many bedrooms altogether then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well that would be one, two, three, four, five, six wasn't it. Si
x bedrooms you see. Done to accommodate the family you see. And - and the aunt we had, bathroom and lavatory separate they were. And what we called a tank room. It was combined tank room and - and a - like a landing - for a back stairs, it was the back st
airs went from the kitchen up you see. To save the stairs - to - to save the wear on the front - with all the children you see, that's what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That was a good idea wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was, oh in those days. He did - yee, he built it - to suit hims
elf you see, yes. Oh yes, that was a good idea for that you see, not today you wouldn't want it but he was - but he did it for his own convenience you see. That was right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did anyone else live in the house besides your parents and your brothers and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - oh no, of course not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You did mention an aunt just now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh that with - she was with - living with us at the time but - she was only - it was only a - she couldn't have been a year or two with us I don't think. I can't remember b
ecause I was a child and didn't notice the comings and goings quite. 'Cos she died soon after we came there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - well they always had a maid in the old days. You know, girls from school, right up
 until - well all - well up 'til she died really. There was a time - period you see when - had four sisters and these - the - just the third, the first two had to be teachers, and the third one stayed at home. 'Cos by that time we were all - a lot of smal
ler children you see to be - looked after, and for some - number of years that girl stayed at home you see. Otherwise the rest went in for teaching one after the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 All of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, yes. See my brother - except two - two brothers went in f
or the building. Mm. Well what he said, the way - way father put it see he'd had four girls - he had three girls and one boy then another girl and - that's the order you see, well - they - they were no good on the building, he couldn't take 'em into the b
u
ilding 'til he was - by the time the boys came old enough to go in he wanted to retire, you see, he didn't want to - see, and we couldn't go in and like build up a business, that way, he was just - but he finished - my father finished almost - as soon as 
m
y eldest brother went onto the building. He more or less went back into business - but that was - that was over the way, to get the - give the boy his experience you see, as far as that was concerned. Well he said if the boys had been earlier, come earlie
r in the family, he'd have had them - them in and built his - you know, business you see that way. But the girls first it - he couldn't do it you see. That's - the way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You mentioned that you always had a maid, would they live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. Yes. Y
es, living in, that was the old style you see. You see the extra - bedrooms, I expect that was why they wanted all - rooms. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Always lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes. Well, not the - the last couple didn't did they, no, they used to come in the morning that's r
ight. The last - the - after the last - after the first world war really. After that they used to come - 'cos they were local girl - always a local girl you see, more or less straight from school they were you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you only have one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. Oh yes, one at a time, yes, we didn't want more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where would she sleep,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well - one of the back bedrooms you see, that's all, one - that's why there were two - there were two single back bedrooms in there you see. And of course that other had 
- had two bedrooms - over the - over the archway. So there was plenty of room for them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where would they eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - well they ate with us. Yes, oh yes, in those days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you feel at ease with the maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well yes, we chi
ld - they were like nursemaids for us, I remember there was one - who had a weakness for taking us out when we were kids, she used to go to - always go to - from the Philog to Roath Park. See we had - had the old go-cart as we used to call it, pram things
 you see, she had a weakness for it. She used to - every chance she had she'd grab us all, put us on - wheel us down there and back see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Quite a long way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 YES, but she was a hefty - hefty girl like you know, oh yes, she was - I remember her - we
nt living in Cardiff, oh she married a postman, living in Kenton and we see her occasionally for years, 'til she was a proper old woman you see. OH she was very hefty for a girl she was. Liked it you see, she - oh it was nothing to her to push a pram down
 to Porth Park. That old road, it was quiet in those days, safe - safe as houses you see
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When you were living here now in Beechwood you had a girl living in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you feel at ease with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well of course they were only day girls then you see. So there was - yes, quite a - there was no trouble then with them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you have anybody living in here at Beechwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I don't think we did, no, but of course there was my sister you see, oh no, my sister was doing it alo
ng then. I daresay, she - she - she kept house you see. Yes. Most of the time I was growing up it was my sister was - was at home see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When you had the maid what would they have to do? Would they clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 A - a bit. Not - they would help when they were babies I expect you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What hours would they work, would you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well, they lived in, they were there all the time you see. Young girls used to come in about eight o'clock in the morni
ng. Not - not much before - not before that time I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What time did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
And they they'd go - well in the middle of the afternoon I think they used to go home then, or directly after - I don't know, about - teatime. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would the maids call your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh as far as I can say - mum I suppose or - I don't know what they'd call her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You don't remember them addressing your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did they call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Just by my name, I was Lew - generally Lew then as a kid you see. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 They'd call you a familiar name really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Yes, well there was a - I don't know whether they did, what they actually said - more than that, well they - they might have said Llewellyn in full sometimes but - wellyn I think they took to calling me at one time, that's the only thing I remember.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would they call your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well the same, all our names you see. Used to call our children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 s names you see. Oh yes, there wasn't all that fuss about it like. No, no, just like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you feel they were interested in you as a little boy, as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I never thought of it. I don't think I ever thought of it, I just - you just grew up in those it was - it was a bit of a scramble 
I can tell you with that lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about your mother, would she give any moral guidance to the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well I - I suppose so, I know what went on between them, not a lot, there wasn't a lot in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were they allowed time to do just what they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Ah, well not so much as they would later on, no, no, they were - they were - pretty full up you see. I don't know whether they had their half day off or what they did, I don't know for certain. I don't - don't remember hearing anything about any days off.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 With you being a little boy you wouldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No, and I wouldn't take any notice anyway, I wouldn't you see, no, no. You see, yes. No, no, I didn't take that sort of thing in much so I didn't take much notice of it you - see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you notice how the housework was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Of course I expect my mother did tell them, she was a very strict sort of person you know, oh yes. Proper old - she'd been a schoolmistress you see and we had - we had it. We - knew all about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the housework now, do you remember how it was done? Would your mother do any or just the maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well of course - in my time had ever so much washing. Always had a washer - washerwoman would come in. Ah, that's right. I don't know when - I suppose t
here were times when we didn't have a girl I expect. There was - periods, I expect it was when my sister was - housekeeping with her you see. I never thought - I never thought of all these things before. You see. No, no. But there was - there was a system
 where a washer-woman would come round for a - a - one day a week you see, maybe either come in - I suppose directly after breakfast, and then go on 'til the afternoon you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would the washing ever be sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. No, no, never did that, ne
ver did it in those days. They'd come in and wash all day for about half a crown you see, in those days. And I don't - of course there's one - one of these girls, day girls who'd come here was very keen, used to - was keen on doing the washing, she liked 
the job you see. And she was washing all times. Some do you see, they took it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about making the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Ah well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, well - I suppose that was my mother larg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 ly but I - I don't know that they
 were - of course my sisters were girls growing up, growing up I think they did - that's the - oh that - that - sister that stayed home, she was a keen dressmaker actually, like - liked doing that you see. Very fussy she was, I mean - but of course -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about mending the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh my mother was a great mender. Oh a great darner too, she'd darn - she'd darn like a bit of needlework, like a - like - oh yes, people used to come \{BLANK\} her darning was admired as a bit of patchwork - like the old
 days you see. Oh she was great on that. Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was beautifully done was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, yes, it was just like a bit of new cloth when she'd - by the time she'd finished. Oh yes, yes. And then she took to - crocheting. The last few years of her 
life she did yards and yards of it and give it all - like her daughter-in-law's and - and - and my daughters you see. They all had it, yards of it, I've got a bit - some of it here now. Oh it was very - oh yes, oh it was very useful you see. On pillowcase
s and things like that you see, yards of it I say and she used to - and then she'd do it and then tive it to this one and then she'd do that, do it - well it kept her busy you see. Oh the good old days, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would do the cooking when you were living in Beechwood?
