Oh well, my - my mother was - would do the most of the cook - oversight doing it anyway with - with the girl you see, oh to help her, she was a - oh she was - I can always remember her cooking, even in the old days, she used to come 
now - it makes me laugh when I think of it now, come in and turn her skirt up, see, tie it up round here, because of course - of course she had to start cooking when she came in - on the Sunday and things like that you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So she wouldn't take it off, she'd turn it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, she turned it up, half way up, I've often seen her do that and pit it up behind you see, hal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 way up you see. Yes, it's an old habit - I - I've never seen anybody else do it actually but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would she put a pinny on over it?
