Oh well - well, not then of course. No, no. I don't remember her wearing pinafores or things over much, but - aprons - often had an apron I think, that was all she wore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would it only be on Sunday she'd do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well, pretty well, it's only she's been to town I expect, dressed up a bit you see I mean that's all. Only occasiona}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420  you see, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh my father's a builder, he did everything, oh yes. In fact he made - he made 
quite a bit of furniture when we moved in here. Oh yes, you see he was a - good - class carpenter you see. Joiners they call themselves then, carpenter and joiner, that was his - trades union you know when he joined - one of the trades unions. Yes, he mad
e
 - of course you see - of course the table he made was only like a plain - like a kitchen table really but he made good long tables to take the whole lot of us in the dining room, it was a big long room. But what he did make is the hall furniture. Oak, I 
g
ot - I - I remember talking once - as boys will you see I was saying - all I want from you, I said, for you - parents getting old, what I'd - what I'd like to have see. I said nothing in this house any good at all, for it was - worn out by that time and -
 and he was - my father was a great man for buying second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
hand furniture actually. He wouldn't buy anything new if he could help it, he'd only one suite of new furniture I ever saw, as a boy. But he made - he made an oak furniture for the hall, see. And I w
as a by running round him then, you know, he was up in the workshop, I was there with him see, I used to come back and - come down and say what I had done see, we - we've done this, we've done that. You see. Well I followed it all, so I liked it you see. 
T
hat way you see. Well he made a hallstand, a hall table, and two chairs. You can see them - after. Ah well they were - they're in - wife has see. I happened to say, it's the only thing out of this house I want I said would be that hall furniture. And sure
 enough I got it.
