\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Because you felt you had helped to make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well I liked it and - and of course I knew it was good stuff you know, hand made furniture you see. That chap down here from London one day, he was doing local for - for our doctor, h
e called in and saw the - one of the chairs, he wanted to know if he could buy it, you see. Well of course - he said to me, yes, yes, you see. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Your father had made it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, yes. Oh he said well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You were a little boy then were you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, I'd be about ten, eleven you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you go into the workshop with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, at - the workshop he had at the end of the garden - back of - just like - where these garages are, only - just on the road you see. He had a shop - like 
workshop on top and stable and - and stable and coach houses below see, 'cos we had a pony and trap you see, and a little - little wheel - cart for - for tip cart they call it then you see, and this horse - 'cos that horse was a pet of mine, I was growing
 
up just at the time and - as he got me a saddle for it you see and I used to ride round for a couple of years. Oh yes, when I was - up 'til the time I got fourteen, got to fourteen, and he used to - draw out - plan the roads out for me, you see, route ove
r \{BLANK\}
 from here you see, and give me the directions on the road and I'd take this with me and off I'd go you see. All - all Saturday afternoon and evening. Well just early evening. But - when I got back my mother used to say afterwards that she was on p
ins and needles 'til I got back in, 'cos - he was quite a good horse, biggish you know, quite a biggish animal really, and I was rather a youngster - I wasn't very - hefty you see, so that - I used to think I was it of course when I - of course the old ho
r
se was getting now - he was pretty tame that way you see. And - although he had been - when we had him first he was pretty spirited. He used to - he'd been with the hounds and he was - when he was younger you see. And - we used to go and take this tip car
t
, go over to Caerphilly mountain, there was a bit of a drift, coal drift you see - just this side of Caerphilly, and we'd go and get a load of coal, went down used to take about - half a ton I think you see on this, many a time gone up there and - come ba
