me then passed the Fer - run up here for the Pentarch and up the old - there was William - Williams the people living in the Heath then, and old Squire Lewis, he had the hounds after him, but these hounds would often come up across the Philog you see. Wel
l
 we're outside the house one day with the horse, horse in the shafts you see, and we had to hold him, you know, like I've seen horses going like this. Well it seemed as if he wanted to be off see. He'd been brought up to it I expect you see, before he too
k to - we actually bought him off a chap - a drive - cab driver or handsome - handsome in those days, see.
