nder these trees, I found it - the thing. But look, here I was on the horse, holding the horse with one hand and an open axe, I was afraid it was going to fall into the horses neck. I was scared stiff. Of course I got home safely see. Oh yes, I always rem
e
mbered it because - because of that you see riding with this thing in my hand. Of course the old horse was quite time then by that time you see, and - I could always manage and I had - I never had any trouble with him. But - the other time there was some 
