\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would the other boys around here be able to go on a horse like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not much. No, no, not very much, I was the last - I was luckier here you see. Yes, only - few - a very few see. Oh yes. It wasn't 
- it wasn't like doing these riding schools now where the kids ride about like that you see quiet. There was one - one little family here living in Togglas and they kept a little pony for their children. Children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 s ponies, they used - they'd ride that as a
 little pet, on the common, you know, with - with them you see, part of the town they were. And all Ballenger's, I tell you he was the - librarian, librarian at the time, John Ballinger. You may have heard - I don't know - first chap in the Nat - when the
 National Museum started up. He was the first - cur - librarian, for the National Library you see. Oh John Ballinger. Very nice chap he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When you were a little boy living in Beechwood did you have any little jobs you had to carry out regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes, yes, I was - one time - 'cos this would be - as well you see up first and clean - poli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 y all the boots for all the kids going to - and these girls all going to school you see. Oh yes, I - yes, started all, I can remember doing it. A
s much - much blacking on me as on the boots you see but still it was there, I often laugh when I think of it now, and then lighting the fires, get and light the fire first thing you see after that. Before - yes, over a certain period you see the - until 
-
 what happened I suppose that until the boys - my older brother started to go to work or something you see, and I'd take - I was promoted from boots to the fire, jobs like that you see. And of course what I - I always used to pad around my father - about 
-
 doing to gardening. See, that was my - I always remember him telling me not to put so much stuff on the barrow. 'Cos of course you know what a boy - I can see myself doing it now, you'll pile up the barrow you see, the more I could put on the better I wa
s pleased you see well I'd get - well I suppose I was struggling and that, he said, don't put so much on, he said.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What jobs would your brothers and sisters have to do? You were doing the boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well I was a boy you see, of course - no, I don't 
suppose they - 'cos from what I remember of course they were always going to school, they had to go to school in Cardiff you see. 'Cos the secondary school, the old higher grade as they called it then you see. What I remember about that was just going dow
n on wet - wet days, stormy days of father going down with the trap, pony and trap and fetching them, going down for them you see, going right down from there to here, it's a long walk you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would they have to walk otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There was a bus b
ut I think they must have walked sometimes, I - when I came to do it you see - just after them, 19 - let me see - 1910, from 19 - up to 19 - four years before that. That's about 1908 you see, 19 - 19 - 1906 I suppose. That's 1910, I think I was at school 
t
here. Well - that's when I got a bike you see. Yes, when I was about fourteen. But the - the roads then were stone you see. And the bike was puncturing nearly every week. So I was walking as often as I was riding. Often I'd walk from here you see to - to 
- to Newport Road and back, I wouldn't allow a child to do it today. See, they'd say it was cruelty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But it hasn't done you harm has it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It didn't kill me anyway. See? That's why I often I look back I wonder how I - did it, 'cos I did then. I use
d to have to come home - and they kept school on 'til five o'clock then. I had to come home here, I couldn't have been home before six, see it's about three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 quarters of an hour's walk you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How far is it, it's about three miles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 About the bes
t part of two and a half, three miles, yes, of course - the same school - same place there now you see, the - the high school. County High you see. To here. That's right - directly on the common. Oh yes, the best part of three miles you see. Yes, well of 
c
ourse when the bike was going I was all right you see but as I say as often as not, especially in the wintertime - you'd catch a bus sometimes you see but I'd walk the - mostly. See? See, I often wonder how I did it but I did it. Used to come home, I'd kn
o
w what I - what I wonder about now is how I did my homework. 'Cos six o'clock - before I could get home. Then I'd have my - my - my big meal really you see, hot dinner you see. Oh they kept up, heated up or something. And then go and do my homework. How I
 ever did my homework I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You must have been whacked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I must have been - I don't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How long did it take you to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 About three - well I don't know - that was - you see, that's right, if I start out at eight o'clock in
 the morning I'd be late I know. See? So of course we had to be - we had to be there really before nine because - the opening or something, or some fuss you know. If we weren't there about ten to nine we were late or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So you had a very long day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
It was a long day, long day, although I wouldn't allow my children - my own children to do a thing like that, of course fortunately when - mine came along they were here in Whitchurch, had a secondary school here you see. No, I
 wouldn't have allowed it. Well they wouldn't - they wouldn't let you do it today I don't think. See, if you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 They provide transport now at two miles don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's - yes, yes. Yes, that's right, over two miles you could claim it you see. B
ut I - I had to walk it. Put that down if you like. Including the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you feel about it at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh I thought I was great. No. No, no, no, I was - I was all right, I was proud of it. I used to rush down there and I was told af
terwards the people used to time themselves by me. On Whitchurch Road - but that was a little later, when I - 'cos I had to go to college after that you see, well it's the same old - same journey you see I had - down there you see. And - at the school tim
e and car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
y straight on with it you see. Whenever I didn't have the - when the bike was out of order you see. And of course that was an old second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 hand bike, and it was out of order as often as it was in you know. Well, well - get a puncture, no, it was the
 road is the trouble. The trouble is the road, old stone roads you see. I remember once - they put down a road at the end of Whitchurch Road like a bad one, see when it was - like Barber church, and they put these stones all across the road you see, a big
 
patch, great big stones, well you couldn't ride a bike over them very well, so I was riding on the footpath see. So when I got to the end a blooming policeman - come out and he's been hiding behind the corner of the shop you know, so he come out with his 
b
ook and all that sort of thing. So I had a fit. Saying, what's your name and number, where do you live and all this business, I came home and I never said a word to anybody you know, I was - I was waiting for a summons, you see, nothing happened of course
. He never - he fooled me of course. I - I always remember it. I was scared stiff for about a week I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You didn't go on the footpath again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well I - not immediately of course. But I couldn't - you couldn't ride - I couldn't ride the bi
ke, I had to get off and walk you see. This old chap come and took my name and number and everything, or - pretended to I expect. I was scared stiff for about a week after that you see. Yes. But - oh I had - but I had my own back on the police. A few year
s ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When you were a little boy you had these jobs you had to do like cleaning the shoes, would you have to do that while you were in school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, I'd go to school later on you see, I was at of course the village school then you see, I used 
to go down about nine o'clock you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But not when you were going to the high school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh no, not then, no, no, not then, that was all done for me then you see. The maids, I remember there was - maids about then by that time you see. Because conditions alter from time to time, as the family grew and - what was wanted you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult to do? Like dressing or eating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well in the early - as little kids when they were undressing the other of course you all - had all of a mass you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would the younger children help the older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh I suppose they did, I mean it was - not - not once a child was able to dress himself I don't suppose you see, it was all a bit
 of a muddle. All I can remember is about - rush to get to school always you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would the maids ever help you to dress or undress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No - well - only with the early babies. I don't remember any - see - seeing anything of that you see, no, no, no, I wouldn't have seen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about going to bed, what time would you have to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Ah yes, well we were always in bed fairly early. Oh right up - my father's time you see always nine - nine o'clock was supper time right from growing up you 
see. All in bed by ten. Yes, oh yes. Oh right - right up 'til the last, 'cos he always - always went to bed at home. Supper was always nine. See you had to be in from being on wandering around you know as kids, in by nine. Ten, supper - that was - that wa
s - that was law, see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well, according to our ages I suppose - you know - always - always - going to bed quite early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would put the children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - well - ourselves - well, all depends ou
r age you see coming along, I don't remember anything - we always scuttled off to bed whoever was there. I suppose the maids would be gone, the day maid because that was - we were - were older than you see. I think the earlier maids - looked after the sma
l
l - when there were only a few small children you see. But - oh that's right, now my oldest sister, 'cos she always kind of - complained that she brought us up, see. She - when she got a bigger girl she wouldn't do anything. She had that kind of a - you k
n
ow, a thing about it you see. She'd be - she had got too much you see. See so that - but of course - I wouldn't appreciate anything about that 'til later. I've heard her say since, I wouldn't remember a thing about that you see. I'd be the victim you see.
 
I think she - I can claim she more or less brought me up you see. 'Cos I was - I was a very weak infant you see, so actually I was - I was - what do you call it - you know, born a bit too soon, premature. See, some months you see, so I was a very small we
a
k baby, in fact the doctor told them they were not to expect me - to keep me because they had lost one or two children you see, that's how it happened in those days you see. There seemed to be no law or order about it. I look back at it - it was pretty to
ugh really. Yes, they wouldn't do such a thing today, you see, didn't use their judgement at all, I can't - I can't understand them. But - there it was. But I fooled them anyway. Actually -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You've heard your sister say that have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, heard that of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 She had to do a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Yes, and - and with the children, she was like bring us up, because a lot fell on - the eldest girl you see. And she kind of got - had that grudge, as soon as she was able to sen went off you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 She didn't like doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, she - once she was finished at - at the college she went on to Barry to teach you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did she leave home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, yes. Well during the week - she come weekends you see. I - I was thinking about it at one time
 for a short period. And you could get a lodging then from Monday to Friday. See, and you come home a short - didn't like that, come home for weekends you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you share the bedroom with anybody when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh I, should say so. Yes, yes. We were always sleeping in bunches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You don't remember how you slept? Who slept where in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well we had a room - the back bedroom I remember was - bunch of us in one corner, another - another bunch in another corner, you see
, there's - there were four boys coming up you see. Different ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you all boys be in the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well in that case when it was like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about when you moved to Beechwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well I was a bit different then, w
e had bedrooms then you see. Two boys, my brother my elder brother and I slept together for years so we were quite - can't remember, suppose used to always sleep -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you share the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, for years, for years and years. 'Cos you see I s
uppose really 'til he left home. He left home, my eldest brother - well just in 1914. Just - just - no, the year before the war it was, 13, 12 or 13 he just have gone. I think we slept right up until then, we were quite - big lads really you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You'd be about twenty-two then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, barely that. Ah yes, was before 1914, that's right. Yes, that's right, I was - I was twenty-two, yes, that's right, then of course -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where would your mother and sleep in Beechwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh they had a big bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 In the front?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes. Be in the front bedroom, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well they had these rooms on the side - two rooms there. They were three double bedded rooms you see. That's right, the girls - two were in one and two were in another one there you see, go up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would they share a bed?
