\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Never had gas, he wouldn't have it in the house. Oh we had a gas 
stove eventually. See? I believe that was after his time though really. Things changed the a lot I can tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well when we were up, from eight o'clock on. Well - of course we had to be out - I had to be out of the
 house at eight, when I was going to school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Can you remember how the breakfast would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would be the first one having breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well of course my father's builder you see, he would get up six o'clock and - s
ummertime and seven in the wintertime you see and he'd be out and come back for breakfast he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did anybody get up with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not unless you're going to work, I don't think so. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would he have anything before he went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I don'
t think so. Not unless he was going - out for the day I expect. I - I - before I was up always. No, I don't think he did - in my time he didn't, he was building around here you see. Didn't do much - didn't do much far away work then, you see, 'cos he was 
coming - he was getting older, you know, before I came here much you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the rest of you, who would be there for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well, of course we were all going to school and - and I think it was Cardiff the Secondary school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about when you were in the junior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well juniors here, well - just get to school at nine o'clock, I just - the older ones had gone and started going to Cardiff you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would they have gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 They would - oh yes, well they had - one a
fter the other as - you see, that much you see as we had to get out you see. But mother would be up and co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
k the breakfast. Oh yes. Yes, yes, the early days, oh you had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would the maid come in in time for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, she'd be up - come in before breakfast. Yes, that's - that's one of the day - day maids, day - young girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you usually have to eat for Breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh the old bacon and egg, you had bacon mostly, bacon and fried bread, that was our big - case then. We were keen on that. And p}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
idge, of course porridge in the winter time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh tea I suppose, you know, I never had nothing more than tea ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you have anything different on any other day, what about Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh well, we always had a big joint on Sunday. So - the old - leg of mutton was the - chief one. Yes, the old leg of mutton was there. The leg. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about breakfast, would it be different on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, we were all there for it you see. Was all together then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you have to eat on Sunday for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 About the same as any other I think, I don't remember any change, any alteration there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about midday when you were in the juniors, when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh we always come home. Oh yes, you'd no school - no school meals of any kind in those days you see. Always come home, and have a meal ready for you you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would you have to eat at the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well I don't know - all kinds
 of things. It was all pea soup in those days during the week. See - used to have - and mutton was another favourite dish, and the old - old suet puddings. We always used to be keen on that, and soup with dumplings. I'm talking about my favourites now see
, I don't remember - what the other things were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What other sort of things did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well everything. One thing after the other. I'll tell you what we were keen on was fruit. 'Cos my father see with a horse and cart he'd go to town, he'd go down Custom House Street, and come}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 
 home with a - a hamper of app}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
les, whatever - apple - apple - of course very funny, he'd come there and put this hamper out on the kitchen floor, somewhere around there, of course every time we'd pass it we'd have an apple,
 for - for about a few days you see, after that we walked past it. And plums when the season came, there used to be, you know, glut you see in those days, you get a glut of plums, he'd come home with a big basket or hamper thing, of plums you see and then
 
we have plums for a few weeks you see. See and same thing applied in those days to eggs you see. And when the season for a few weeks you can get 'em twenty four a - twenty-four a shilling or - you see, shilling a dozen - before you see, and they'd - they'
d
 come up generally 'til you got - occasionally, I - I can just remember twenty-four - they've been twenty-four a dozen a day you see. Things like that, these don't happen now. They don't allow it to happen see. So that's how - oh we did very well, we were
 always - you know good to - for food. That way, I often look back at the old days, we couldn't live like that today, not - the stuff that we had, we had you see. Oh yes, was all the fres}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 h}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420  stuff 'cos I mean - a great gardener you see, always had plenty of p
otatoes, you see, and - the garden stuff and beans, and of course in those days you see there was plenty of manure, we had our own horse. I never planted anything without planting a lot of manure with it too you see. And we - we used to have beans where w
e couldn't cope with them. Giving them away and all the rest of it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would your mother preserve any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did a little preserving. Oh yes, not - but not very strong on it. But some people were very keen on it in those days. But not very - becau
se the old plum and apple - was - was the stand by in those days. Because we had these great jars, you know, seven pound jars, fourteen pound jars. In fact I - I was only thinking the other - I think I've got one old jar about you see and now they're - no
w they're }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 antiques}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
 you see, 'cos - well I've thrown them away, smashed them one after the other. 'Cos we had crowds of them at one time you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That say last year's trash is next year's antique?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, well that was - that's what's happened you s
ee, that's what happened - I mean I've seen that process going through you see. Oh yes, very funny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you have your main meal midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would you have the rest of the day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, it was just tea and - and a supper. Supper nine o'clock sharp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would you have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh tea, was always plenty of cake - there was - tarts and things you see, fruit tarts. And naturally bread and butter and jam as kids you see, rice puddings, things like that. And some of 
these - apple dumplings in season, we - I mean we did very well by - cy compared you see, very good - good for children anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about an evening meal now, supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh that was just a bread and cheese affair. Yes, oh yes, that's all, nothing very special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Can't remember, only tea I think, oh and cocoa they do a bit of. Nothing special I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, and she never did that, she was a - no. I've never known
 her to do it. She - she wasn't a great cook. See, she never claimed to be, she was a plain cook she said she was, yes. That's what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh did - by - according to the fruit you know. Some - when we had those plums you kno
w of course and - and raspberry - the last - one of the last things I did with her - was making raspberry jam, 'cos I grew - I had - got a whole lot of raspberries and we had a good crop one, year, and was only she and I were there at the time, my - young
er - brothe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 r was tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
ching away and all that sort of thing, and - I did the doings under her instructions you see, that's why I always remember it. That's right. Yes, but of course that's fairly recent history.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would she make any pickles when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 She used to do a bit, not a lot. The old pickle - few pickled onions. But we didn't have great quantities. Not like some people used to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would she make any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. No, she wouldn't do any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well no, used to have the old - it was in summertime, make a drink like lemonade stuff with - fizzy, you know, a bottle of magnesia I think it was. Used to make a fizzy - fizzy drinks. Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 She wouldn't make ginger beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, never made any of that sort of thing, no, no. No, no, there was a TT business you see, never any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You did mention that you grew some vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 And fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 A little fruit, oh yes, gooseberries and currants things like that, 
not - we didn't grow apples until later we had a bigger garden, 'til we came here you see. About 1900 when we got here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 The stable would take up a lot of the garden wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 We had a couple of apple trees here, and did very well. Had some ve
ry good trees some years. Very good fruit. See and apples now when they got about ten years old - they gave a tremendous crop here, you see, oh yes, fair does.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you have any tinned vegetables or tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 The tinned fruit, yes, the old pineapple chunks were the - favourite if you remember. Yes. Yes was very good on that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about dried vegetables or dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - oh, well of course - you mean I suppose raisons and things, those - oh yes, always at - Christmas time especially see, that way.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you keep any livestock for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not very much. Once I - Once we had a little go at chickens for a few years, but it was only a few - that was back here say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No, no, 'cos my father was a builder and busy you see with all work, so we never had that sort of thing. I remember the neighbours up on the Philog had - used to have pigs, one after the other, on either side, one - a little pig stay at the back - end of 
the gardens, but we never did, 'cos we had the horse you see, stable and beyond my father was working you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well - same as we do now, there's always a big joint on Sunday, well that was cold meat for
 a couple of days you see, it lasted out, and then we had soup - and - we used to get a - I don't know - because this boiled mutton was a favourite thing, you know - ribs - a side - I forget what they call them now - but I used to like that, we had white 
s
auce with it, and all that sort - certain dinners I used to like that way. And we always had some supplementary during the week. Bits, you see, what it was, liver was a favourite thing I know. And fish was fairly regular in those days, used to come round,
 old fish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
man I remember. We had - herrings you see, herrings were pretty - yes, we were pretty good on those. We had quite a lot - regular you see, very regular. 'Cos the old chap used to come. And we could always get fresh - you get 'em fresh you see. An
d mackerel, I haven't seen mackerel for years, we used to have a few of those - they came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Very seldom. And I don't think until latter years you know. 'Cos mother - see we were a good crowd and mother was alw
ays cooking, good cook you see always, in that plain way you see, but we had plenty of it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 We didn't poach round here. Not to say - that was only - the lack of opportunity.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
I don't know of anything like that. Always was - 'course we didn't go in for luxuries. What I call plain - plain living you see in that way but plenty of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well I never noticed but I'm sure he did, used to get - we all had plenty, it was only - the only sort of thing - I tease the wife about you see - the tarts. But you see they were all - they'd make two tarts on a Sunday th
ere would be, and there were - eight - ten of us you see. Well the tart - tart cuts into eight. And of course there was always a few bits over, wasn't enough to go around, but we always had a kind of z half piece for second helpings, we kids you see. But 
we - al}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 lowances, one each you see, onl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
y had one piece of tart, that's all you see. See, occasionally if we were - you occasionally get a second helping, it was the half piece you see 'cos - that's all the - spread you know but it's only in I mean, like you 
know, tarts, luxuries like that see. We'd always fill up with bread and butter if we wanted to or bread and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you allowed to talk during the meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well you could talk, not obstreperously you see, we had to - watch our step a l
ittle bit, see. There was plenty of discipline though, father. Used to have - he had the old cane now when we were young, to threaten, oh yes. Never used to, not that I know of. But of course with the whole crowd you see had to be kept quiet a little bit 
you see. But wasn't a very strict discipline like that. And we're very good. He wasn't - you know, he wasn't very stric}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
. He was strict in the way I mean - even right up when they grew up they were kind of afraid of our father. Well he was strict you see, the - and he was - firm see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you afraid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No. No, I got that I - I was - and they used to call me Benjy sometimes, because I was a favourite with him you see. Well I used to follow him around, I could - you know I could see myself doing it no
w you see. I didn't realize it quite but if he was ever doing anything I was round there helping you see. And - I didn't notice - this was when we were grown up you see, and come back after the first world war - and - my sister was home, my youngest siste
r
 you see and my youngest brother there, and we thought we'd have a celebration, a whole crowd of - youngsters and in the chapel we had a crowd you see then, and - they want to have a party, have all these people round. They said, you ask him. You ask him 
if we could have it, see. They were afraid of asking, because - he was getting on a bit you see. I had to do the asking you see. So I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So the others must have thought that you were the favourite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well that must - oh if you ask him he'll do it. Of course -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did they think I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, of course - yes, oh he said - well I only thought - think we're going to have a couple of kids, you know, other friends round Sunday, you know, one day over the Christmas. But I had to do the asking see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did they used to call you Benjy in front of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, no, not - not the regular thing but - they'll - just - when they began to notice what was going on a bit I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh no, no, there wasn't much in choice, you had your - that's you - you have what you have - I suppose - as I always said to my own children like that, see, we had what we were given and like it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh finish it up of course, just - that's right. Children never left - never left very much - much of that. 'Cos I'm a bit soft with my - my own grandchildren coming along you know aren't they, they're very 
slack on that sort of thing, see. Got a way of - asking what they want, what they want you see \{BLANK\} oh I'm thinking she says. What was available.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You just had it put in front of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, that was - of course it wasn't there, we couldn't g
et it you see. It was take it or leave it you see. But mind there were some things I remember now, some}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
things I didn't like you see. And I didn't eat those, but only - a few things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh they were left, no, no, the
re's no trouble about - oh I can't eat that you see. It was mostly cabbage at one time, and then later - and I never got to eat parsnips, they're too strong a taste you see, and car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 
rots, I didn't - I like the carr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 ots raw but I couldn't like - eat them cook
ed, until the - when I come back from the first world war I eat everything. See, but up 'til then I - kept a number of things, there were a number of things I didn't like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 And your mother didn't mind that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, not that you see, it wasn't -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the others, could they have likes and dislikes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh they would treat us all alike in that sense you see. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to
 wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well - I couldn't remember exactly. Well, I - you could ask for it, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 A bit yes, if - if it was there you see. Not a lot on the second helpings, it i
t was available you see, you're not - couldn't just say well you can't have a second helping of this or that you see. Well - a lot - it's a question of - the quantity you see, couldn't be prepared for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well you did really have a second helping of the tarts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
In that case, yes. Yes. And I tell you what used to be a great thing with the joint you see, you had a lot of gravy, the whole joint got roast - have a piece of bread dipped in that, that was an extra like - second for kids who can always eat
 of course, that way you see. But only - only like that, you wouldn't - no, you wouldn't have as I - as I've seen them here - down here sometimes, go and get another plate full absolutely - almost you see, and have another second dinner almost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you expected to hold the knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well yes, oh the - my mother was very strict on - on the doings - table manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you have to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - of course one half were always on a long - either a b
ench - would be a bench or so - sofa we had, sit on that you see all on one side, a long table, could take us all in, we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Could you remember how you used to sit around the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where did your father sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh he'd alway
s the top end you see, and my mother at the - at the either end, see. One each end of the long table, and you were on the sides.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember how you sat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well mostly in age group - age - order age roughly you see. Oh yes. Yes, the olde
r - well be further away, the youngest up to the - the father I suppose or the mother, I don't know, oh well, I - I expect it varied you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How did the younger children manage before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - we - I - I should - I should remember in a way but I don't recall about the eating very much you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You don't remember the younger one, where he'd sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh the - no, well I suppose - next to his mother I expect you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would the older sisters or brothers help the little ones to feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Yes, I think they must have. But it's a funny thing, I never seem to remember seeing any of that bringing up of children. I just didn't take any notice you see. No, I'd always go out and play soon as - soon as they get down from
 the table, out in the garden you see, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You said you followed your father around a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I said - yes, oh yes, I was not domestic in that way you see. And a funny thing as we grew up older you see that - they used to say to me 
- you know youngest boy - brother - brother see, he had a lot of sisters - older than him, they were bringing him up, you see. With us it was, oh get on out you kids, play, you see, but he was - round with them. It was a very funny thing, I - after I come
 back now after the war you see, they go with the washing up, he'd go out and help them, they wouldn't want me, you go and read, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So the older girls definitely helped with the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes. Oh that - to that extent. But that applied to D
avid and Edward you see, but of course they were good step - younger you see. They were just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You did mention that one of your sisters said that she thought that she was a bit resentful in a way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, well that's the old - eldest sister, my 
sister Hilda and she brought me up, I think I was - I was a - responsibility to her see. I was very weak as a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So they must have helped?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well they must have, of course we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How would the meal be served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Ah yes, well the things w
ere - there was - the old days then it was all - always a - a dish of course the meat, and - and the vegetable in vegetable dishes, if you remember. See, but that's gone out. There's a big soup tureen I remember. Great big thing you see. And that of cours
e -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you help yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, no, we never help ourselves. Oh no, of course what - kids would be - a dozen - a half a dozen children you see at any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would serve the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh my mother. Mother always yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would she serve first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I don't know, I don't know they went in order I suppose, according to age very roughly. I've no idea about that. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the servants that you employed, where would they eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well of course we were such a crowd,
 I think that quite often - sometimes - but I think mostly had afterwards. I think that it came to you see because of the crush we were. Well you see - well you sometimes ate it, but mostly - to my like - years I can re - recollect clearly it was after I 
think. Yes, always - it was afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would they help at all in serving the meal, help your mother to serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, not in the room. No, not - not - not at the table, no, no. You see things changed after we grew up, and like when we - aft
er the first - after the - after the first world war you see, and habits changed a bit. Everything was - you got then - you brought a plate - that the servants had done - helped done in the kitchen - in the scullery you see, and brought in you see. Things
 changed from the old - the old idea - with the big joint and - and the vegetable dishes and everything all served on the table. And it's gradually - that's gradually died out really. And it did with us you see in last few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would the servants have different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, no, no, all the same you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well, for some people - no, she wasn't a great - she was a bit formal, she's an old schoolmistress you see, the old style. And - bit pa
rticular you see, of course we didn't have that difficulty of course, but I know people that used to - a bit of a - a - well staid like you see, but - with a - a staid manner, bit formal you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not a lot, no, she was no
t a - not demonstrative person, no, not at all. No. No, it's only - oh well criticism or the - you know, like with my mother that I could make. Well if you'd call it a criticism, that was just her style, her way, she didn't - she was all right in that way
 you see and - all that, but there was non nonsense, and no fuss. You see she wasn't Welsh, she was English, and you didn't get that temperamental stuff what you get you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you feel there's a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh tremendous difference, I know it y
ou see and of course - we're the same you see, the Welsh people you know - that way, they carry on, my mother was never - but we never had that nonsense, you see. Didn't mean a thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Your father was Welsh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh he was Welsh of course but 
of course he - he wasn't - he wasn't a great talker, in that way you see and he wasn't like that, you see, he was strict and - and he was always busy you see. And in his public work when he wasn't doing his own, you see. Well that was a great game you kno
w, parish council I - I remember, he - he'd be talking, but he wouldn't come home 'til after nine o'clock, nine to ten and then you'd hear him and somebody else talking at the gate. Fair old tal - talkers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not a lot, no, you sort of - sort of would - you wouldn't talk too much like that you see. No}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 , no. No, no, you'd keep it to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 ourself rather see. As you - especially as you're growing up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not - no, not like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Not - no, not - not so much - show it like, but he was - he was - he'd look after people look after us like the holiday business and that you see. Bu
t - he was always busy and you know, and - well he was good for - he was good for a game and - fun, if he was in the mood and things were on you see, he'd play tricks with - play tricks on the - children I remember you know and - oh yes, he was - he was a
ll right like that. He was full of tricks you see and - funny old sayings and things you see, yes, yes. Oh yes. Oh he's all right temperamentally and all that you see, but not - not this - not very much nonsense about it you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 If you had any worries could you share them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. No, I never talked with - to my father much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh with very much - well that's as I say it was more you - they were all afraid of him in that wa
y you see, was no - no - not familiarity, no - none of this familiarity business at all that you get today you see. See and in my case they started calling me pop and all that, you see and that's all there was to it. But no, if I'd have done - said that i
n those days there was a stick for me or something. Well I never thought of doing such a thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You said you didn't actually have the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, no, we didn't ever use it. There - there was one around that - you know, in reserve like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you think that was the difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes. Yes, oh yes, 'cos we never - we never had a cane here or - and - and the other - next - my grandchildren and that, they have - less discipline in that sense you see. They've much more freedom still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you think it's a good thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Up to a point. As long as it's not carried too far. You see, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well yes, up to a point - I mean, well 
you know what children are, we used to have our little quarrels and things and that but they were - well suppressed, just you know - not - not much rioting that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. No, n
o. No, no, no, shouldn't do that. No, it was always topped, of course the kids would do it first of all you see. But not much, there wasn't much of that with us, we weren't - you see - never much in the way of quarrels and all that sort of thing. Of cours
e - what I - I know the things went that I - I never knew of 'til afterwards. See?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You were not aware when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I was - as a child, but they don't tell you anything, I found out lots of things I should have been told I never knew - 
until after I was married. Then my youngest brother - now funny thing now, 'cos he was in with the - with the girls, his sisters you see, a lot more and he knew lots of things that I never heard of. 'Til after it come you see, in between those girls as th
ey were growing up you see, there's always bits of fuss and bother, and I was quite - blissfully unaware of it all, see, 'til I was told about it years after you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You must have in a way been living in your own little world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I was a bit, yes, but - must have been a bit withdrawn I expect you see. But that sort of thing, but that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What kind of people do you think your parents helped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well he wanted us all to be teachers and that you see, he was a gre
at - education man you see, and the School Board, was always on the something coming up you see. Oh yes, we all - one after the other, see we were all sent - sent to the High school you see, before - of course there wasn't very much of that around here th
e
n, only elementary school here you see, I remember him coming to me one day, would you like to go to the high school? Oh yes, oh yes, I'd like that. Next morning I was hauled down there you see, all the schools were half empty in those days. I'd just go i
n, start away the next morning you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But you had to pay then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh pay, yes, yes, yes, three pound a term. That was the fees then. It kept the same all the time as far as I remember, four or five years, yes, never paid any more. Things were steady in those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
