ilog here you see, whole string of kids, see we used to fill two pews there like, 'cos he was - he was secretary - he was the treasurer of the church then you see. Oh yes. And my mother of course was very strict. See? I expect she used to give us - before
 
we were old enough to go to chapel used to give us scripture lessons on Sunday evenings. I - I remember that 'cos we used to love it, these stories you know, about the old - Genesis stories you see. Used to go and race get - race to get the book for her t
o
 read it. Tha-age you see. Oh - and my young - my grandchildren just the same. As we told stories I used to - I was one Sunday morning here when they were staying not long ago - two books here I've got we shared first prize for scripture knowledge - from 
