hought of looking to see if it was the Echo or what paper it was you see, I wasn't old enough for that. But you know, up until the following Christmas see, after that, I - I was dead convinced that - that - that there he was you see, 'cos he had left that
 paper behind, but by the next Christmas it was all gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would make the stocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Our own stockings, oh yes, so - well, in my time of course it was the older girls see they were up - teenagers you see, and it's there like, a whole row of sto
ckings behind their bed in their room everything was done you see. So we were left to sleep all right you see, and - we had none of that waking you see. But they were all there and the first thing in the morning we'd be there and there's a whole line of s
t
ockings right across the back of this bed you see, all filled up see. Oh we did very well there. A funny thing, I remember one year I had a - a set of - skittles, see, about - these nine pins business see. And - oh how marvellous, great things you see and
 
I thought oh dear, and I kept them for - eventually I - I - I just - I don't know how they disappeared but eventually they went you see. And years afterwards when I got older and I used to think to myself - I've never seen any skittles so big. They're all
 
so small now I thought see, 'cos - of course I realized afterwards of course it was what I imagined, they were such - they - they were like trees. I said, well of course not, they were so big as I - imagine them all the time see, it's the big ones that I 
h
ad you see. That - that's all the go, he was very good on the - on - on - and Christmas tree now I'll tell you what he used to do, he used to dress up as Father Christmas with - a little do in the chapel. I remember you see he came there dressed up, we'd 
b
e gone on, I didn't know him. See when you were small you were deceived you see, he come in this white beard, he had this thing for years. Big mask and a big red - some old red - over it, overcoat thing you see. And he did that for years see with the Sund
ay school, people have said. See. Oh he was good, he was - he was like that I say, for - for playing games and - and tricks you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You said a Christmas tree?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - no, in the chapel, the one for the Sunday school one, yes, yes. Yes, yes. O
h yes, that was - that's a big thing, a big thing in the lives of young - youngsters then was the - Christmas with us, and the Whitsun treat at the chapel. Those two - made our - our year like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What happened on Christmas? Would it be Christmas Day you'd have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh - well it was in the evening on Christmas Day, yes. They had this Christmas tree. You see, in - in the chapel, we had a little toy off it you see, and - always an apple an orange, an orange it used to be you had to come home 
with you see. That was the routine, 'cos - when we were bigger we didn't want the Christmas tree, we'd go in there and - get our orange and run off - when we were - we were fourteen you see. I remember doing that. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well the piano was a big thing. 'Cos my mother did a little - a little teaching at the piano. When she was - yes, before the children - before - before my time you see. And they all learned, my sister was quite good, my eldest si
ster, she - she started - of course they - they wanted it for playing hymns in the chapel you see, in those days, very small. And - she had to - they wanted her - she had to just learn one hymn during the week and play that one on the Sunday, she started 
-
 as far back as that you see it was. But my actual - that's a little bit before my time you see, when I - when I knew her she was - she was - the organist of the chapel until she went to college you see. Then. And then - my youngest brother, he was good a
t the piano and he - he took on the organ in the chapel. But I was never - I - I'm not musical. I - I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you learn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Tried to. But I - I haven't got a note you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How many of you would be playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well only one after the other, of
 course there were the girls, there's - the three - the three older girls, they all learnt to play. Were not great musicians, the eldest one was the best one. And then my - this is Gwendoline, now what is she - she'd be the third one, and she went a littl
e bit more - keener - to do a little more playing. I remember the - we had some neighbours came there, a man who - who was a keen musician and he used to come in and they played, used to play duets and things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would teach you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well my sisters tried - tried to teach me you see but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who taught your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh there was a - a Mrs Adey living in Church Road. Was well - oh yes, they used to all go to her. 'Cos she was a very strict woman you know and all kids afraid of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You mentioned that you mother could play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Only a little, she never played in my time. She became a bit too busy and all that you see, she never had - there was - I never saw her touch the piano, I didn't know she could play. See, I didn't
 know, but I heard it all come out you see. But the children all played and my - and some of them quite well you see - My eldest sister was quite a musician that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, he had no music, that's - I suppose that's where he spoilt me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not much. No, the girls didn't sing, not like - no - no soloists you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh round the piano, yes, it was mostly - well I 
suppose the hymn singing on the Sundays and then - I know they were very keen on then - at one time there was the old nigger songs, you know - minstrels, yes, nigger minstrel songs you see were very popular. They had a hymn book, a - song book, with a lot
 of those in I know you see. And you know, Swaney River and all that sort, all those things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not a lot. No. Not in my time, 'cos my father was - grown up a bit - well he - he was getting heavy and all that. Not - not - not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But he'd play tricks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh tricks and that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - play tricks on us a bit, I suppose. I always remember - well there was only one I remember, trick he played on us, oh - 
yes, he had a habit of - of - showing how clever - how clever he was, he'd put his hand on - a back of a chair, kitchen chair, not quite so high as that you see, and put his leg - put his leg over it you see, and of course we couldn't do it, we couldn't r
e
ach it you see. Things like that you see. But I remember the last couple of times he tried he nearly fell, he was getting a bit - big you see, he did, he came very much to the front at one time you see, and he was getting it - a bit beyond him you see, an
d
 his mother - mother warned him about it you see so he stopped it then. But the one trick he played on us, I can - I can remember it quite plainly, this used to happen about supper time business you see. Oh he could - thought he could run up and down the 
garden, how quick he could do it, the length of the garden you see. He'd do it so many times in - so there wer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060475\charrsid2756420 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
 were timing him you see. And he was out there and of course the evening dark, and he'd come in, he'd hit the post once you see. 'Cos I suppose he
 just stood there for a few minutes - and hit it again and we thought he was running up and down you see. Until we all tumbled to it you see. He - of course - of course we - children were different ages you see from quite youngsters up you see. Tricks lik
e that he had you see. And old sayings mainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were there any books in the house?
