\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - not very often but at times you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would they come here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Came here a bit yes. A bit. Well when - especially when they had visitors, but it's only one or two occasions. They had a - there was a - my mother's - one of my mother's brother - was li
ving down - Kent - Gillingham, he was - of course another carpenter on the ships carpenters you see, down there. And - they came, I remember quite distinctly coming here, staying with them you see, then they came from Llanduff North across here, that - an
d there was with him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
a cousin Edwin - a boy my own age you see, and - I remember, well he must have come across I know once or twice perhaps you see, I can just remember one or two when they were all - all together on the lawn there, and - then - when the w
ar came on - I came - I was - I went over to Canada, just about the beginning of Dec - the beginning of the August, and - the August the war started you see, and I'd got an appointment there in - Toronto University - and - went there over so and then I - 
I
 joined up at - by the - by the end of that year, of course they were all called round where you'd join, all the young fellows of course we'd finished - finished our course there and - and three - two or three of us - and we all joined up together you see
.
 And I was back here then in the following - following summer. May. IT WAS AFTER May I think, left Canada in May, about June or July - back here and I was stationed in - Folkestone. And I went to see him - in Gillingham, and stayed with him a couple of da
y
s you see. And that's about the only thing, and then of course there was another - the - boy - boy in Wareham, he was a little bit older. And he was living near Lanfudd North then, in Cardiff you see, and then he went - he - he was in the Army, called up 
y
ou see. But he is a little bit - he had a - a stuff - a - a fixed joint, fixed elbow. And he - he was always like this, you'd never notice you see, he'd sit round all that time, but when he had to use this arm it was always like that you see. Well what he
 
could do and he was in - he could drive a car. And he went as a chauffeur to some general or other round here so he was only in the war in that sense you see. And those are - were the only two cousins - that ever had any dealings with in my life. See? The
r
e was the other one, there was a John Lewis living on - North Road, and he was a - a carpenter on the Good Estate, and they were - in the building line. Now one of his boys, a Fred Lewis - went - worked with Turners, and he was - he was - well my eldest b
r
other and they were both studying then at the Technical College you see, the building work together. So I used to hear about Fred see. But I never met him, only once or twice at funerals, of - of latter years you see. But there was none of growing up toge
ther or any family or any - there were no - we were quite alone you see. That way, yes, very thin.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I - well not in the ordinary way, used to run little messages up the village and all that but I'll tell you one thing
 I did for a number of years. Had this pony - we had a old pony and trap you see and I used to have to drive my mother into town on Saturday mornings, and she'd do her shopping in town, and I used to - draw up by the free library here, in Hayes Road, it o
p
ens part time you see, and I'd be there with the trap, she'd come to me with her parcels, see, and I'd stay until she wanted to come home you see. And I'd drive the horse and drive the horse back you see. 'Cos she couldn't drive the horse. He wouldn't mov
e
 for her anyway. And - of course - oh - I had the instructions not to use the whip and not to do this and not to do that you see and I used to grumble like mad she said, 'cos I - wasn't allowed to make the horse go a bit you see. I was just one long grumb
le she said. That's the reputation I got. Oh yes, that - that way you see. I had a good time really you know, you see driving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not a lot. It - it - when we were down at Barry once or twice. That way, but
 not a lot, no, he wasn't one - of course he was always so - you know, full up you see, with his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - yes, well he didn't believe in Bank Holidays. They were - thought up in his time you see. He'd carry on his bus
iness, and of course he couldn't have - wasn't working you see. In fact - used to go round on his business on this - Bank Holiday Monday same as any other. You see, no, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you go on any outings with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not a lot,
 well I suppose we did in the younger days, used - used to take us up the Garth I remember in the pony and trap you know at that age you see. Up the Garth I suppose was a favourite one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You said you did go away for a holiday every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes. Oh to Barry, oh yes, that was - that started, yes, yes, he would take a month off then, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You'd all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh the whole family, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That was lovely wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, oh thi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 s case I was thinking of yesterda}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 y was I've just wr
itten a book and he's - he was - a boy, he was brought up in Leeds and he went to Scarborough, on the same stunt he said, every month, every summer for a month, took a house you see. So they were doing it up there the same. Well that was later really, onl
y a - younger man you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was quite original then probably, your father taking a house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was a bit and - and quite uncommon you see, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Because it was an empty house and he'd have to knock up a bit of furniture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That
's right, and then take a few light things you see, what he could take on a cart you see, tip cart, a couple of journeys - he would do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You wouldn't go anywhere else would you, it was always Barry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, only to Barry. Well you couldn't - it - was too far and all that sort of thing you see, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days? You mentioned you went with your mother into Cardiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well for one period, yes, yes. Well - oh only playing around here, and build -
 if my father was building anywhere we'd be all over his - building round you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 The houses were just near really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Mm. Used to take us round - the sort of thing we'd do - you see, when he'd go - he'd go down to the timber yard, and we'd go dow
n in the cart with him, and the timber you see. Things like that, we were always looking out for that sort of outings you see, that's what it was, connected with the business. I remember the last time I did that, it wasn't he but - he had a - one of the m
en you see, they used to do that, and he had a load of bri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
ks, only a couple of layers you know, you could sit on flat, sit on these bricks you see and still in the cart in the front, and it was on Pontbach Road, you know the - it goes down there to the old
 houses there, on fact he was working on that house, what they call - Williams's live there - oh you'd hardly recognise it now, it was an old red brick house then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not Pontbach House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's what is is, Pontbach House it was, yes, yes, he built
 it - he built - the - you know it's rather long and narrow. Yes, Grove Hill up there, that's right, yes, that's right you see well - we're coming down there, and - they'd been taking a - they were putting a - a drain you see on the roadside, on the road 
t
here so half of it was up you see, you know, this ditch, and - I don't know what happened but I suppose - it was only a trace horse, the harness must have broken. It was coming along with the weight of this thing you see and snapped it down, and I can rem
e
mber I was in this cart, but I kept in - in front of the board you see. The - the things, the horse - got away, the thing - and the shaft broke. See but I was still in the guard. Just clinging on to it you see. I never got thrown. And the old man - the ma
n I - he was a little old chap, driving you see, and he was pulled over. He went over onto the road and bang you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was he hurt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 He must have - I don't remember. He must have been a bit, nothing - not very serious you see, but I remember this l
ittle accident. But of course I was clean, I was in the guard the whole time although it was nearly tipped out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So that's the sort of thing you'd do on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, well we were boys you see, always round with a -;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was interesting wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, oh for us, yes, yes, yes. Climbing round the buildings and - playing with odd things you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well that was chapel. Three times a Sunday. Oh yes, always. Yes, yes. 'Cos we used to walk fro
m the Phiolog, way back in those days you see, when we lived in the Philog, all the way down and fill - fill two pews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you have different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, Sunday best. Oh Sunday best was a great thing. And I've always kept it, I've kept it r
ight up, see, and - they say I was the only one that used to - look after his best suit. I folded mine away in the old box you see, 'cos the others would - oh - I always looked - I always - I was always proud of my best suit you see in that way. But it wa
s definitely Sunday. Sunday best you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
I didn't, I didn't have much of a game - not - not like - what do you mean, football and cricket and that you see, no, I never - only school. The school games you see. What I what I f
ound, of course I shaped up a bit at - hockey, see I got in the school - team, house team or something. But what I found you see - if I played out hard, by half time I was done in. And I was no good the other half. See? I wasn't a - I was never strong in 
t
hat sense as other boys, most of them you see. They're mostly big - bigger and all that sort of thing you see, and if I played - very enthusiastic and play - I was all right 'til half time and after that I - I'd just stand like you see, I was pulled out. 
I wasn't for that, so I never took - big games you see. What I - when I grew up and I got in my teenage I was walking, I could walk all over the - place off on my own you see. That's what - that - that was my big - spent all my time you see. T}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 he only thing we had was - ragg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
 - ragged game on the common here on Good Fridays. When you see all the boys of the village get together then you see. Boys who were doing other work and apprentices and all that you see. And we - put on our oldest clothes and tear 'em to 
bits and - oh - every Good Friday it was the regular - for a number of years you see. And I remember one year was doing that and it was very very hot and I - there were - group of three boys, myself, and we - kept here as a bit of a group for years and ri
g
ht until the first world war really, that's what broke it up, see and we used to all go off together, us three boys, and the thing to do on Good Friday was to go up to the Garth and we'd walk up the old canal bank you see. Well I remember that you know, i
t
 was very very hot, and we played this game in the morning, and we could hardly drag ourselves up. We got so at each - each - lock we'd go and sit on the old lock bar you know, every - go and rest there and then go on to the next one. Eventually got up th
ere but - oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So that was every Good Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, for a number - number of years you see. Oh football - well I suppose the rugby, yes, oh yes, the rugby, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about playing games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, oh no, no, no. Never hea
rd of such a thing. No, no, no. It wasn't done either. Nobody ever did it. The only thing it started up with - when the gold course opened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That was much later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh much later you see, oh you wouldn't - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But you'd play that game of football on Good Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, Good Friday - very funny thing - about that, Good Friday was never like a religious day with us. No, and you see the - non - conformists in those days didn't celebrate you see. Every Sunday was a Good Friday - if you argue
 - argue with them you see, and - and they didn't believe in keeping festivals you see. But that has grown, now they do. You see? This last - twenty years. You see, we've made a big - point - now of Good Friday, and to - to me now Good Friday is an extra 
Sunday now. You see, I wouldn't miss a - now we've started this service since the minister came to Bethel - he'd just been appointed, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 only a few weeks really, started}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420  with us and Good Friday came, and - he says, look, have a united service. I don't know whe
re the got the idea, whether he done it before somewhere else you see and he got all the other ministers - only Wesleyan and - and - and oh yes, they all said, yes, he just did - the old telephone call and it was done you see, and they've kept it up ever 
since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh nothing. Oh it was only - I never knew it was Sunday - I never knew it was in any way - just a game of foot - and this football match, and that was my schooldays like you know, bigger boys you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes. We weren't to do a thing. Not a thing. Only sit and read. See, we'd read. See, but that's all we could do, supposed to. But go and play in the garden and all that, something like that but - I don't suppose we're playing, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - I should say so. Sunday, yes. Oh he was the - he was the secretary of the - the treasurer of the church when I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Baptist. He was Beth - Bethel Baptist of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 English Baptist that is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 English Bap - yes, English Baptist because my mother was English you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Your mother would go the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, yes, all family - as far
 as she could with the children, they came too. She did say once she never went up to the village for ten years. See the early end of - the family you see, there was a baby every two years, and you see she'd her hands full.
\par 
