\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well I tell you 'cos once I said something about
 - I remember talking to my mother - one evening about - I think it was Welsh Nationalist or something. And of course I was in favour if it was new you see, coming up. Don't tell your father that. Don't tell your father that. That was the attitude. 'Cos h
e wouldn't he wouldn't \{BLANK\}
 for his generation, oh yes, never dreamt of such a thing you see. And - and Welsh Nationalism was coming new and I said well I said you're a nation, they've got a language and all of it you see. We've got that, we've got every
 right to it, I said, see. Just thing like that. She said, oh don't talk - don't tell your father that. That was L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
oyd George, self government for Wales. Well the paper - but - yes. Oh yes, home rule business you see, but that's not what - Yes. Yes, that's right, that's home rule. But not - not - not so much the nationalism you see. Break away you see.
