 yes, 1910, yes, yes, my father actually was the agent for one election, with - just - all I remember of that was the burning up of the old papers after it had finished. I didn't know whether the candidates here used to talk about it and they used to say 
w
hat a wonderful man he was, Williams I think his name was. Charles - was it Charles Williams? A name like that. I can't quite remember, that's the first one I - first actual ones I remember actually was Brace. William Brace here. See? And he was Lib Lab i
n those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember your father when he was the agent, it must have been quite an active time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh it was, yes, yes, oh well he dod he all the foings you see, I remember - as I say all I remember was a whole lot of papers being l
eft behind, and burning them up, at the end, what was left over see. Old posters. See? That's all my recollection of that you see.
