Not on her own, not - not like that. Oh not all the family, dad did all the outings - beyond the holiday - you know, family holidays. Oh no. And he wouldn't do very much I remember going to London once, that was a great do. There was some deputation I t
hink it was really or something. And he went to a conference, well he was with the - Foresters. He didn't do much with them but he was a member of them and all that you see. And - had some business with them. And I think he was like one of your Grand Mast
ers something one year, in those old days - when they used to parade you know, dress up and parade you see, I remember them coming here to the house in Beech Wood, on horseback an old chap, see, Forresters, they would come dressed up.
