My father ran the - National - War Savings business here. During the first world war. Yes, I remember coming there with that see. And he - and when - when I came out of the Army he sent me on it you see. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about a funeral club or a sock club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well of course - he belonged - what - he belonged to the - joiners - mason - Carpenters and Joiners - Society you see, a trade union
 that was you see then, and then this Forresters. The foresters was a club you see. Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That was a benevolent society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Really, it was so he had - 'cos I know he was laughing you see in the last few years, he had a pension from them. He was g
etting ten shillings a week. See? When he didn't need it, but he had it of course. Well he paid all those years you see. See. And the Forresters the same. I don't know whether you got any money from them or not. But he was a member of the Forresters you s
e
e. Those are two things he did belong to. I've got some of the old regalia - that he had, he was a - you know, a - chief Forrester or something one year you see and all that. And that's how he came he went to - a place - Oxford I think they had a - you kn
ow, big - annual meetings or something. Big congress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh - yes, well quietly but there was always a bit of a squabble. Oh yes, that's never never much. The sisters all right, but I - but I - my b
rother was two years older than me you see, and actually I never really get on with him. In fact - my father didn't really. When it came to working - he - he couldn't get on with him at all. A bit of a character in that way my - my - older brother, he was
 
only two years older than me but - he'd put it over you if he could you see. I know what I remember once oh he'd borrow some pocket money, never get it back you see, no - no, I didn't, you know, this business you see and he was two years older and I - I n
ever used to fight you see but of course it causes bad spirit and I - and it's been all life that way you see, so - he'd take advantage of you if you can you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the younger boys, they were quite a bit younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh they're a good deal younger, they didn't interfere, didn't know anything about them until they'd grown up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not at all, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You've been a bit of a lone wolf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Aye, that's right, yes. Yes, 
yes, yes. In that way. 'Cos I had one sister who was - who was - invalided from what age - twenty or so, twenty or so she'd - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But when you were children, before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. No, none of that, there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What was it like here between your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well we were all right but as far as I was concerned I never used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There wasn't one you were particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No- No. Just - I know, they were - paired up a little bit but no, it's none - non
e of that. No. No. Just my - the boy - he was a bit - and he was older you see. And - he didn't stay in the school very long, he went on - to work, he wasn't very - he wasn't - that type quite you see. So I never really got - see, and then - and then afte
r
 - well he was - doing work and I was in school I didn't see much of him only on Sundays you see. Oh no, we never did much, and what happened with me, there were - there were three of us, there was a boy, neighbours boy, one living here and one - used to 
live on the - \{BLANK\}
 he moved up to the parade afterwards, and we three stuck together in that way. On Saturdays and we were like pals you see, we went off. We went off up to the Gewenneth, those three you see. So it wasn't a family business you see. And t
hat was from the age of about thirteen or fourteen you see. So -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who did you play with, it was these two boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Those - are the two other boys, we formed a little group you see, Saturday evenings and all that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You didn't play with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. No I never did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Or your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. No. The age groups, they too - were all too different like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where did you play when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh we had the common here. Had the common her
e, we were - we were well away for that. Go right down there, down to - beyond those houses onto the railway you see, old Phillip's fairs, we called it then, there was the farm across the road you see. Oh no, we had plenty of - play in that - in that age 
y
ou see. And then there was a - there's a - family alongside here had two boys. Just one - one of them was about my own age, I was a couple of years young - older you see, well we'd be all playing around here then you see. But funny thing now my own boys, 
m
y own brothers, 'course my other - that one he never played with us - then, he was never a kind of with us in play. He'd gone off, he - I can't - remember how - he - because he - oh he did go to the - he went to the higher grade for a couple of years but 
he didn't make any shift you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Two years is nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Of course at that age you see. It is, it's - it's a lot you see, wouldn't play with him - wouldn't play with those kids you see. No. Because it's quite a difference, no, the different age. Y
es. Yes. Oh it's a big difference, yes, we don't play the same games quite you see or have the same ideas you see. Sometimes of course I daresay but not a lot. See? In fact - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - allowed, we often were but we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh - of course I - I remember - I can actually remember still - I must have been seven or eight - dressing up, this red Indian business with feathers, and oh I can - actually remember - I - I
 could - now - I remember beginning to feel a bit self conscious like. See, and foolish see, because I never did it again after that. But up to that - up to that time I did tremendous, you know, oh marvellous you see, it was the thing, see. But I can reme
m
ber now the - the day like when I felt - a bit silly actually, and I never did it after that see. But up to that time of course I was a red Indian right enough see. As my - my boy can say about his child, see. But he's always - you see, he's - he's a red 
I
ndian all the time, a cowboy or something you see, at that certain age. But they seem to come to it younger now. Then we did. Because I was - old enough to remember - you know, what I thought about it see. I must have been seven or eight or - or - oh no, 
I must have been - when I came here. I was nearly ten, nine or ten, I was still - still at it you see. It was a simpler life you know really. Must have been.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well, we were a bit particular but we
 didn't have much choice in a way. There used to be a - a gang from Birch Grove - lot of people original inhabitants in Birch Grove - were mostly - farm - market gardeners, there was old John and Byliss, and there was different odd fam - different type of
 
people, Bayliss's were very rough, we were scared of them most of us, and used to come down from Birch Grove to the same school you see, but we were scared stiff of them you see, and their language was awful. See, oh aye, rough there you see. But we would
n't - wouldn't see them afterwards, we would come here and - we were afraid of them see actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well we - not definitely, we had - you know, neighbours here were all right in a
 general way you see. No, we didn't have - their children - not that stuck up business. There was a bit of that about I know in those days, I know we had one - had one little boy - one boy brought up here - he never played with anybody. Was always around 
dressed up. In the ordinary way, had kid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
gloves on most of the time I think, you see, it was very silly of them you see. But a very funny thing about that boy. See - now when he grew up, here after the war and all that and settled down. Of course he was muc
h younger, I've known from my boyhood, this is later you see. But - I met him in - I was in a bank one day and he came in and he - and - oh Mr Lewis, and chatting away like mad you know, like an old uncle nearly. I had never spoken to the boy - in my life
 
until then you see. He knew me and I knew him you see, but I think it was his parents more than - you see, the boy himself must have been all right in a way you see. And he never played - he' never played with the other children. See. In a way - yes, but 
he was kept from it, he wasn't allowed to I expect you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, we didn't - I didn't join - my youngest brothers - yes, no, yes, well the youngest of those - I don't think - no, David it was, the se
cond one - he was a scout for a - boy scout for a bit. But they went about - they weren't organised here when I was - there were no scouts in my time see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was after the war really?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, well not - it came up but it didn't - it wasn't - it wa
sn't here in Whitchurch, see, we didn't - everything wasn't organised here and people hadn't - there was none of that here about 'til a bit after this you see, but I was too old by the time I got to know about them you see. So I never had - oh no, the Sun
day school was the only thing - only - social life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How did you spend your free time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I don't know that we had any free time. We had our games days, we played football two afternoons a week, football and hockey. And cricke
t you see in the season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not very much. No, I never had - only the cats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Had you started collecting your stamps and coins then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, that was my - I never - had anything - see, in childhood, because - as I say, i
t was all work and my father's work all about you see, and - we didn't have any money to throw away. I never - there was a penny a week pocket money - for up until I was - you were quite big you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You had a penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 We had - yes, we had this, t
hen gradually came on to - see I never had more than sixpence - a shilling a week eventually, right up 'til just before the first world war and I was in coll - going to - begin - nearly in college of course, but all the time I was in secondary school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you spend you pocket money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well I had to keep a bit - I used to do - little things that I wasn't - necessary really but I - well my - own - I - I had - I'd buy my own collars - ties you see. You know, didn't want to go and ask my mother
 for money but - I kept a little bit you see. Things - that was all - and then the only thing was bus fare to town if I had - still had it on a wet - on a wet day you see, had to try and keep a - a three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 pence for that. And - and - a big collection in the chapel, that was the only thing. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you have to give it out of your pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh I would do at that - I would do it anyway you see. You put - had to because once you had a pound you had to use it see. And I gradually mounted up - and
 we - but I never had a - any - any hobbies like that - took a little bit of money and like that I couldn't - I would just throw it you see. The boys were - it used to be done I tell you. There was the old - Boys Own paper, I took that for a couple of yea
rs, as I was growing up, that was the only paper - a boys book and of course read about it in that you see, and that was all, see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. Oh a little bit, yes, a little patch of garden you see and put my seeds in. I grew c
ornflowers, I remember the cornflowers, I never seen such tall ones since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What sort of classes of people were living in Whitchurch then? Which class would you say that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well I suppose you'd call the small - business really. Smal
l business class wouldn't you. One man business - you see. Only employed casual labour, no permanent - no permanent employees you see. You see, only used to build a house or two at a time then. See, and your men would come - and do the job and finish that
 house, you'd stop for a while you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would you say the people in the similar class to yourselves then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well it would be the same sort of - there are people about now, small builders. Not so many, dying off rather - recently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about then when you were children, who would be in the same sort of class as you in Whitchurch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Yes, well it would be I mean perhaps - shopkeepers, or - people like that you see, and - well - you see - most of the people in Whitchurch worked in Cardiff y
ou see. Well our neighbours here now, one was an accountant for instance, another was an engineer, for a time you see and others, there was a family of - well they were they were like mechanical engineer - you know - working down the town you see, that - 
that sort of people you see, not - not a labouring class and there were none of the - none of the Mill and Griffith people living round here. You see, we wouldn't be like - they were the - the - manufacturing you see. And the tin workers, tin}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 workers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There were none living here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No. There's only one man I knew, a collier supposed to be living here. Well I've heard of two actually in my time. There was one living on the Philog. There was one - well - there's - a little more recently living
 up there in the village, I don't know exactly where. But that was the class of people we had, you know, went up with the houses roughly, you see, semi detached and that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of own sort differently from people of another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Some - there was a - there - the last it was Squire Lewis, that was the only one, only man we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I thought you mentioned that last time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes. Oh you touch your hat to Squire Lewis, yes. Yes, he was t
he only man. Only person who did, he used to - you see he used to come to the school, he was like a - a - a governor of the school I expect on the council you seed and he was - 'course, that's right, he was -, and the school board, had an old photograph h
e
re, he was the - chairman of that you see. So he used to come into the school occasionally, when he came in of course everybody stood up. That was the only person it was ever done for - here you see. Of course long be - before his time the Squire business
 all stopped really. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was there anyone that you called sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That - that was - well I suppose you would - your - your own schoolmasters practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Anyone you'd call madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, not - not - not in that way. No, no, no. No, no, just Mr and Mrs that's all. No, no that was all out really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in that way? Touching their cap or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, none of that. None of that. No.
