I don't suppose - their own kind I suppose, their own business, I mean when they were in the chapels you see. There was a big man - Tom Samuels was quite a big - well - that's funny, Phillips the farm, they're both - they w
ere both Bura people., you see, but where they'd be - they would be considered a bit bigger you see, trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
people. It's only been - these - what we call - smallish trades people today and - and actual working people you see, say working class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you think the people were, what were the classes then? Did you think people belonged to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well as far as class is concerned that when you - you'd get of course the trading classes you see, like your farmers you'
d get and then - other - shopkeepers, and you had the - of course you had the clerks. There were a lot of people here and we didn't know what they were doing - very definitely, but they were something on the docks. You see, they were clerks in different f
i
rms and - offices and that you see. But it was quite - I'll give you a - was living next door, his - his sister - or sister-in-law I suppose came in to live, and I hadn't seen him since he was a schoolboy. Bert Jones. And it - it came out he'd been in the
 
same office in Cardiff all that time. HE WAS a few years older than me and all I saw was a boy going down to town you see, a big boy. And - 'cos - 'cos I remember I was awfully jealous, he had a knew bike, I remember seeing his - him and his brother. They
 
were all just about two or three years older than me you see, well here they come swanking on new - polished bikes you see. I used to be very jealous of 'em. And that's about all I knew about them you see. 'Cos I - I though he was - I thought he was on th
e - working in Taff Vale railway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 The docks were very busy weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, oh yes, of course, oh yes, docks people you see, it was always - that was a big ambition, to be something on the docks. Up 'til the 14 war, see. Since then of course it's all gone different, you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about teachers then, who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well - they would be a little - more of a class by themselves in that way you see, a little more educated, well with other teachers something li
ke that you see. Although - of course my father of course being on the school board I remember one - one old - old headmistress of the infants who used to come and visit us a lot at one time you see, but after that - it's not you see. We've been getting a
s
 a matter of fact - the - most of the head teachers come to Whitchurch come from Swansea way. Because they've been appointed by the county, you see. And - the girls, I told you they stayed with us - college friends with my sister you see, well she was fro
m
 Swansea, see. Nearly every - most of the ones - head teachers here have been Swansea women. Since my time and for that reason - every since - that - became county you see. Since 1911. The county see. Get the appointments you had to know all the counties 
y
ou see, and - our count - the - the old - the old - squire was our county council here, of course nobody ever saw him, he was living away out most of his time you see. And so they had no reference on the county in - on the committee you see, and so that b
u
t - up - around the Swansea areas there were a lot of ministers were on the councils. You see. They put 'em on the council there, well of course people were in their chapels, see, the minister knew them, there was all young people like you see, well of co
u
rse you get new appointed, they were coming down here as head teachers. Whitchurch teachers never got an appointment. No, not - there's only one eventually did but it took him all his life to you know to get - get in on the - he was out you see, he used t
o complain well he had to go round you know, get - get round after these council}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
ors see. Eventually he got the head with the senior - with the senior school you see. Well I know it was terribly complained about it here, bitterly you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the employers, you had several employers living here, you had Mr Roberts from the Mellon Griffith works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, he was - a manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who did he mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well I don't know. We had nothing to do with 'em more than they used to - you know, I d
on't know, I think they were Robarts - first they lived here - one lived - they lived here first of all in - this road here. The old man anyway. Not Roberts, Davis, was Robert Davies, that's who it was, Roberts. Robert Davies was the works. And he lived -
 
that's right, they lived first of all by - just behind the chapel there. Just past the Lloyds bank, and then they went to live in - St Petrarchs on Park Road, big house there. See. No, well - we never saw much of them, we - they - they were in their busin
ess you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well - well of course you would get - there would be - you would get with the - better off people, but there were also others you know. Church people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the people going to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Yes well - you would get more - well - well Bethel actually was - was mainly Mellon Griffith men when I knew it first. Yes. My father was one who wasn't one you see and I know it was - there was this bit of against - he was - it 
was very cliqued up, especially when the - when the - Labour movement came on. I knew two or three - young men there and they were - leaders in the Sunday school, but as they grew up and Labour moved on, and we - we lost 'em. They saw them - they was comi
n
g out Sunday afternoons having a - and Sunday evenings having meetings on the Comon. Labour meetings then. And that's - that's really what's killed it, the - free church movement round here. If - well - for it's strength of numbers you see, we had all the
 
working people, and they were also running the chapel they were, you see the secretary I know was - who was - was a - oh old Sidney Jones you see, he was a - worked on the Mellon Griffith on the works you see as a works manager he was you see. Well he was
 
running the chapel you see and then they had a say, and it was their life you see, apart from the - the actual - labour you see. Oh yes, they made the numbers. Although of course we went on - when things got - right up until - almost up until the second w
orld war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Up 'til the first world war now you think it was really mostly the Mellon Griffith tin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well of course they were the most - more - they were the biggest bulk of the population, so really it had to be you see really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the other chapels here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well the same sort of thing. Yes, the Tabernacle, yes. The Tabernacle is more - more the old Welsh families there. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 They were the only two chapels when you were a boy were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, there was Ar
rarat, Bethel, well you see there hasn't been any change since my time. Only some of these - well really fancy religions have come here and there, but I - I - they don't - they don't stick very much you see. And the Plymouth Bertheren have come since at T
innapark, things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where was no Catholic church here was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no Catholic church until this - this is quite recent you see here but - Catholic priests used to come out from Cardiff you see 'cos \{
BLANK\} said they called on her once or twice. But - they never got very far in Whitchurch you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 In Whitchurch then did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living, or do you think there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, well - well of course it would go
 by what they earnt you see as the wages were low in the early days, were all much the same, they were. But - as I say you'd get a little different with the - the - these docks people you see, that come on you see, it would be a little different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you think they felt superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, a bit, they were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Compared with the Mellon Griffith workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well that's it, you see, it was the white collar workers you see - and - and they were what they called blue collared \{BLANK\}
 manual workers you see. There isn't a lot of difference but there was a bit you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was there a bit of difference then when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, yes, yes, you just got - that was only - there was that - there was that feeling a bit you see. Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well - it depends on their - the - their - their behaviour you see. There was - the only way we - bit you had is from Birth Grove people. When I say Birch Gr
ove - yes, that's Birch Grove up here you see. There were a lot of market gardeners and they - they were really - mostly come over from - Somersetshire way, places like that you see. And the Bayliss - the Bayliss families, there are one or two about now, 
I
 suppose I should be careful what I say in a way, but they were - they were pretty bad. Johns - Johns weren't so bad - so far as reputation was concerned. But they were that type you know. There were a few lad - a few people, they mostly settled around Bi
rch Grove, the old - they were the old long rows we used to call it. Up - up Back - Back Road way, you know, only a few old cottages round there you see, and working on the market gardens. You see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There were a lot of market gardens there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh ye
s. YES? it was all this - right up - right from - market gardens from here onto Curtaiz, all along Whitchurch Road, I remember it as a - Armours were big people, well they're still about now - there. And the last was a man called Noble. You know that part
 where -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You felt that those people were rougher did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, they're a different type of people. Yes, now the boys for instance - yes, yes, yes, a gang, a bit of a gang from there you see, they were - they were different altogether. Much rou
gher. And we were half afraid of them. See? And so were the teachers. Oh yes, some of the teachers were. Oh yes, rough class they were, they - they wouldn't go to school you see, the boys used to stay away from school, that sort of thing you see. Not all 
of them but - they were amongst them that - that kind you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were there some families then thought of as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well, it was - it was - yes, it was mostly chapel going on for those that didn't go to chapel. That you'd see that you see. Or
 - or - or - going - you know, used to - go to the public house a lot you see. 'Cos that's all there was, yes, you get these people - I remember there were a gang used to come - when we were boys, they'd come up from the Three Horseshoes - Three Elms here
 
you see, right opposite, and - they were regulars you see there, and they'd come out at nights, about - nine, ten o'clock they were kicked out then and - all come out - come along the road singing. And we kids used to come home, keep on this side of cours
e and then we started - shouting after them and that, that sort of thing you see, imitating them you see coming that way. But you don't get that sort of things now, you see. Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There were families then who didn't go to chapel were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 A few. Yes, but they weren't - that is to say they weren't - we didn't regard them as - respectable you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who would they be I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well it all depends if the man took to drink a bit you see and then of course - it'd be the ordinary wor
kmen you see, there was an old chap Broad there - like that, you see, but they'd be the same people, they'd - there was you see - there was old Caroline, an old woman there had let herself go. See, we used to shout after her. See? Yes, she'd be around the
n
. My mother taught - was telling us - that she was - one of the toffs of the Whitchurch as they used to call them, when she was a young girl. She let herself go through drink round the public houses and all the rest of it you see. Well you don't get chara
cters like that today. You see, you never see them. There were one or two about like that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well of course there always was a distinction, I mean - oh you was - t
hey were very - they were proud - men were proud of their work in those days. Good carpenters and good - good - painters and things you see. Good masons, good - a good mason you see. And of course then there was - there were labourers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you feel there was a difference, people felt there was a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well there was a difference a - a - a - a bit, well of course as there is now really. And trained - just a trained man or an untrained, you see they'd be apprenticed in those days, and
 good - long apprenticeship too you see. Oh yes, there was quite - quite a marked difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Up to a point I suppose, but - I mean people like - I don't know - do
c - doctors and people like that used to think a - you know, a little bit different you see. But - it's - or professional people would be - regarded differently, just as they are today to a - up to a point you see. Of course the difference - difference wa
s
 more marked because - although people - they hadn't any education at all to speak of you see. The ordinary working class people in Swansea who left the elementary school and some hadn't - you see, well and - and others of course professionally trained an
d so on, they would be totally different you see, but - but that has blurred considerably and it was blurring at the time so to speak you see, oh yes, it was breaking down you see. Breaking down gradually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh she was a teacher you see. And they were 'cos - 'cos they were a little more educated and they were quite - kept themselves apart very largely you see. Yes, yes. Although of course her bus - her family, they're al
l - the - the - the men of the family and ours too were all carpenters. Practically all carpenters you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Why do you think she felt herself like that, was it because of her own job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not because of her family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, no, they
 were just - just - no, it was just - no, no, just the - her work you see and then - it was a church school and the teach - teachers came from - they were - they were like - unpaid clergy nearly or they were assistants, you know, they worked under the cle
rgyman and all that sort of thing you see. That was - that was - church school you see and they always kept themselves up - off a bit like that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well it was - well it would 
be according to - perhaps a - a matter of money really. A man in business would make a bit more money, he'd - he'd get it that way you see. It'd be the same people of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember anyone who did then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Kind of got on in that way? There
 were a few I suppose, I don't - not markedly, no, I don't think anybody kind of started from nothing and made a fortune, that sort of thing didn't happen round here very much you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well not - oh - you - you - I suppose you mean more like the squire would be, a landed gentry and all that, well he - he was about the only one you see. And Co - Coley's of course they were - they were people got up with business you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You didn't think of them as real gentlemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well not in that style, they weren't county or they weren't landed gentry you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever remember anyone being described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not like that. It's only - of course the squire - ther
e would be Mrs Lewis you see. But - 'cos I remember - talking to the - what was - I didn't actually see it but of course he - she was - on the - at a political meeting here you see, big Tory meeting, her - Whitchurch hall, and she was supposed to - have s
a
id that - they weren't wanted now. One of the last meetings that they - the squire was there and she was there and - of course they were - everything - she wasn't - she wasn't regarded you see, she was - she was almost crying they say there, well she felt
 
she wasn't wanted. See they were very good to her in that way you see. It was going, all that we and it was never very strong here because - you see - this - part was - wasn't strongly - rural completely rural you see. It was on the edge of Cardiff, we ha
d
 people coming out here, gradually coming out here see, and the - the railway, the - the - the Nellon Griffiths works being here, there was an old fuel works in Maindee, we weren't really out - truly rural you see, and - we - our society wasn't based on -
 on that you see, or based on the farming really. You see. We've always - we were - Cardiff -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You weren't dependant on the squire and his lady as they would be here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. No there wasn't - no, not at all, 'cos you see he wasn't only a - well -
 only had a - I - I understood in the land, because he - it was very poor, but in some - some of the properties a bit of coal mining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 They did own a lot originally didn't they, the Lewis family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - oh they must have, yes, a couple of branches of them you see. There was a branch here - at - what did they call it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Mary Ann Lewis, Disraeli's wife was one of the same family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes. Well that - that goes well back beyond you see, yes. Yes, yes. It's the same family, oh yes, the same family, that's right. Q}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 ite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 They say Disraeli used to stay in a house up here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's right. That's right, stay there and go up from there on you see, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I don't know whether it was Green Meadows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes, it was
 Green Meadow. Yes, oh quite, yes, yes. Well this was long before our time you know, you see. That's - that's real history.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 This Lewis you were talking about was just about the last wasn't he of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 As the squire, yes, Sir Harry Lewis never wa
s a squire here, you didn't know him, you could - what - he was - he lived here for a while but then - he finished up living in - a house in Pentarch. See? What do you call it, Birch - what they call it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember seeing a policeman when you were around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, oh well we had our village policeman. Williams, Seargeant Williams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well, he was a big man of course with us, Sergeant Williams. The first one I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you think of him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh of course were always afraid of the policeman, boys, or children. Always afraid of the bobby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Why were you afraid of him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh - I suppose you were taught rather that way and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your mother ever threaten you with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well not - no, no, we had never any dealings with him at all like, it was only - and his boy was in the school with us, one - see, Williams's boy - it wasn't - that was only - only childishness that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh I think he was a - quite a popular man. Oh yes, hear a lot about him, old Sergeant Williams, this that and the other. OH yes, of course - he was popular I think amongst men, amongst - people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No, my father was a builder you see, he built - he built it - that's right. He built - this house on the common and went and lived in one. And - then here on the common when the family got too big you see. He built that - came - we came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh our life was always a struggle. My father, oh yes. You see - business was slow moving in those days, you only put up a few houses at a time you see, a couple of - that 
you see, and - then it'd be just - oh no, he always had a - a struggle, but he never - he never - caused any worry or that about it, well I think my mother did all the struggling, she used to complain a bit you see, but he - he was all right really. He wa
s
 - he was - he was good at business, in his way you see. I mean when - when he - when he died of course he had a - he had a big overdraft you see. But he - of course he died at sixty-nine, he hadn't had much time. You see, he - he - he didn't mind - I mea
n
 he - he - he'd work with the money you see. There was the debt there but it didn't affect our living, except that of course you'd never throw any money away, and you wouldn't - I mean a lot of people who flash stuff and - spend money, more than he would 
spend. You get it today, I was in a house - I was in a house the other day, you see, there was a chap - he's - well what he's doing now and - a great help is - is -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you as a little boy feel that your parents had to struggle, did you realize it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes. Oh you were - we knew that much. Won't go as far as to say we appreciated it much as a small boy you see. It was only a question of - business you see. But - we weren't pinched in any way in liv - on living, as far as we were concerned you see, 
we always had - ourself - quite - quite good you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill, or out of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 He was - no, he was in business you see, he'd got his own business, he never had - he never had that trouble, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever have to get help from the parish or any charity or Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh, just - just ignoring them I suppose, there was nothing to do with them, that sort of thing. It was mostly I think in the question of drink in those days. There was a drinking set you see. Public house people and the chapel people. That was the only di
 - divide as far as living was concerned, in that way you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was there a lot of drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well - there must have been a good - a good deal, but the trouble - the only thing is that it showed you see. The Saturday night business you see, some all drunk on the streets you see. I don't call it a lot. But we don't see any of it today you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 People can drink at home now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well of course and - that sort of thing, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Went to school, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh we started then actually at three. In the infants. Two to three you went to school then. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Do you remember what time you went in the morning then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh it was ordinary school hours. Oh yes, nine, oh yes, 'cos we'd near you see - I actually started - well - I'm a little bit mixed up, I start here at \{BLANK\} not far from - from - well from Philog really, a little dis
tance, and then they built Birch Grove school, and I went there for a short while. See. And then I was back here at the age of - well all the boys school started when you were seven. Standard one they called it then, at seven years of age, they like trans
ferred back here - to the boys school was here you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So the first school you started, what time would you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh nine o'clock, the school - ordinary school hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What time did you come back, about four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I expect, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 About - take a little bit from here, of course - from here to \{BLANK\}
 well not long, used to go over the fields you see. Ten minutes say walking about yes, yes, 'cos we took all - all that because there was a brook along the road so we had to - it took us a long time some days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You mentioned earlier that it was a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was, before my time though. It wasn't a church school in my time. It had been changed over, the Board took it 
on before I - I may have been born but it - I wasn't concerned in it, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 A board school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was it mixed or just boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh boys. It's always - it's always - always - separate in my time. YES? there were - three divisions there in the old \{BLANK\} school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who went with you to school when you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you go with your older brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh I see. I can't remember - I can't remember exactly when it's as a ne
ar as that but I always remember just going, my brothers and sisters were going there too. You see. Well - there was always a crowd of us - going in - in bunches you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh home. Never any - never any school meals, never - no, I never did any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh just took it for granted I'm afraid 'cos my mother was - oh my father was a school board man you know, and all that, it was quite - the thing you see. YES? I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes. Well - I liked - I liked some of it you see. I'm afraid I just took it - without much - liking - much liking or disliking about it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, well I neve
r - I - I - I - I didn't take much notice of the teachers really. There was only one teacher I ever kind of liked in any way and that was in the secondary school. I took to him. He was a nice chap he was. But as for the rest, well - I was perfectly indiff
erent in that way. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well - I expect they did a bit, but not - not a tremendously, not - no direct -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well had the stick -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 This was in Glannant, the first school, before you went to the high school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Ah yes, well you'd get the stick of course, you'd get - or the cane, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Cane on the hand that's all.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would you have to do? To be punished. Like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh don't know, make a noise or play too boisterously you see or - I don't know ever I did - ever - got into anything very much like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I can't remember. I don't remember it anyway, I don't think I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There were no girls in your school at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No, no, they were a separate department, no, they were a separate department you see. They had the ground floor - they had the floors of the school and boys were always the - one above you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, they always - they were always interested in it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well they'd never - never much fuss - about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh of course my father did as - in his capacity as a governor you see, he used to come - for to check the r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 gister on that day, just occasionally that's all, once - once in a year perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 He'd be bound to meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh he would meet them, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well everybody ever did, it was all the same, they - there were a few - a few private schools round here. Yes. There 
was the - Mellon Griffith - these - \{BLANK\}
 there was another one I think. Well that came a little later. But - only a - there's a few of those, some of those - some would go off - to other schools away, and one or two came on back, came on here as they grew older you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, I don't think so. Not - not obvious anyway, not - I don't think there was much of that. I didn't realize it anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about the fact that your father was - a governor of the school, did it make a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well - didn't make any difference, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You did mention earlier that there were some gangs in the school, there was the Birch Grove gang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh only that, that was about the only lot, they were different - and was a little bit of a - that way you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not that I know of, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh well, yes. Yes, although that - that was - that was something coming up you see, the - Penarth, the Penarth County School - and before that they used to get a - a - few boys each year would go scholarship - on - to - to the Penart
h County school you see. That's three or four boys - would pass and get a scholarship to the Penarth school, see. That started a few years before my time. See? But my father didn't want - didn't - not - we called it Penarth school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not Cardiff high school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No, not Cardiff high school. Penarth was the county you see. But - my father didn't want me to go so far I don't think. He started me on his own in that way you know, in the Cardiff -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So you went to Cardiff High School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I went to Cardiff High School direct you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What age were you when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I was thirteen. Yes, it was a bit late really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That's what we'd call a direct grant school now I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 I - no, no, it's not - no, it's not - it's the only
 inter - there was the Intermediate Act. YES? IT'S NO - so it's not a direct grant school. It's - mind a bit special - they always - they always treated a bit specially Cardiff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 It was the old intermediate when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes, intermediate school, it - it was called that under the intermediate education act you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Was it a day school or were there any boarders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh day school, no boarders. No, no. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Boys only, yes, 'cos - well there is a girls school corre
sponding to it you see. Well in the same - same buildings now. Well they have gone out - the girls school has gone out Yes. Yes, they've gone there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How did you get to that school, you mentioned earlier that you walked and you biked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Cycled, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 And you would take a bus sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There was a bus - for wet weather and that you see, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 How long would it take you if you walked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well, about three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 quarters of an hour at least. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 If you biked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh I'd do it about - less than half an hour, I did it once - supposed to have done it once in thirteen minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That was the record was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That was the record yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Who went with you then to Cardiff High School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well there was nobody e
lse from here. No, not from Whitchurch. At the time I went, I was the only - only child that - from the chapel who was going to a secondary school you see. Actually after that of course it increased considerably. You see. Came on like - between the two wa
rs, that's when \{BLANK\} but before that it was - unusual. I was the only one that I knew - of che}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
r you see. Some of the boys had got scholarships to go to Penarth with, two or three, you see, each year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh in the school, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would you have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There was as a rule, had mostly sandwiches. Anything that happened to be - bread and cheese sandwich was the main one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did you think of that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Pardon? Oh it was a good school. Oh it was a very good school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you like it or did you dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well, I say - I liked it all right, I mean I was proud to go to it in a way you see, because it was a bit different from the others and all that sort of thing. A
nd - it was the first form master, old Davey John, I know I've heard of him, David John Thom - Evans, D.J. Evans he was known as, and - he was a very nice chap. Very nice chap indeed. And I used to be able to learn his stuff without any effort whatsoever.
 Because of what he taught you see. But as for that that's the only man I ever - only teacher I ever liked at - they were all just the teachers and masters to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not really. Not - no, no, y
ou - just your work, it was all - pretty cut and dried there Oh yes. The only man who used to talk - preach like that was the headmaster, old Jeams Swar. He was always on about conduct. Yes, you see we used to go up in this school, going up and - going ho
m
e, of course a lot of the boys would go on City Road way you see, most of them were really living in - Roath Bettws you see up there, and of course we'd a - a big crowd, we'd get in peoples way and used to get complaints about it you see. They do - get th
e
 same sort of thing here in Whitchurch at the top end you see, come all for half an hour, and then he used to go on for us - every - every few days we'd get this you see, he's had complaints. He'd get up and - oh - walk along as though you had - business 
to do you see. As though you're occupied, not to go sauntering around and getting in peoples way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you have punishment there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There was no corporal punishment there. None. It was only there were report - what they call report system, the pun
ishment was to stay in from playing football and games. We had games two afternoons a week, and - if you were reported for misbehaving you were kept in that afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There was no caning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 There was no - no corporal punishment whatsoever. See, a
nd there was no need for it there because the other was pretty bad for boys. Boys can't - a boy can't play football - when everybody else is playing is pretty tough you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What sort of thing would you have to do to have your games stopped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Wel
l sometimes very little. All depends on the various different masters, they punished you for different things. One would - if you - if you'd neglected your homework a couple of times, he'd - he'd report you for it you see, and you'd have to stay in. Quite
 
a complicated house system we had then there, that way. And you had - that'd be for almost anything see. Oh yes, because then Saturday morning you'd have to go in - they'd keep you in - an hour late or sometimes at midday Saturday, 'cos we had a Saturday 
m
orning school, and that was a terrific one that was. I think the only once it happened to me, I don't know what I had done, something or other, and we had - I remember one master coming in, he didn't live very long but he punished everybody for everything
 and for nothing. Whereas we - most of 'em - nearly all our class, all the boys coming with him, we were in nearly every afternoon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Why was that I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh it was - oh he was a crackerjack you know, he didn't stay there long, he wasn't there m
ore than a term. But he was a tartar. Punish everybody for everything and for nothing really, you can, you know - I forget how he used to get on with it, but he had us in - every afternoon for weeks see. I didn't worry too much. But - of course a child ge
t
 hardened to thing like that because - although you were in there we were kept in it was pretty slack you see. IT WAS - WE just played around mostly inside. That's how we - we - we - the old boy will get a - and - and - and like make his own fun out of a 
thing you see, it wasn't much punishment, only like that we were there you see, tied up. In prison.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did your parents say when you got home late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh they were - we didn't get a - we - I mean I couldn't get home late from there. The school was
 five o'clock and I come home about six. I was never late from that, I'd be asleep I think. It's a long day you know. I mean I wouldn't allow it today, I wouldn't let a child of mine do that sort of schooling that I did. Oh dear no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes, oh yes, they watched us all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 But they were never - never hard about it. No, if I didn't - do very well, a report like we had, I wonder what's going 
to happen, nothing would happen you see. No, no, they were - they were very good, I mean I've no complaints at all. I know very often I deserved a - a - I probably deserved it, I never got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no, not - only with - father took me down there first. You see, had no - nothing to do with this, that was in Cardiff you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would they ever meet the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. No there was very little of that sort of thing in those days. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did the other children in the high school come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, they would - were similar and - and mostly - well and some better, really, 'cos, some of the bigger - you know, we - often thought of it since too - the - what's the big - shippin
g people - hm - just can't think, people - names go from me and that's a thing that's - last few years. I've known them all my - see - Seagers - Seagers people well his two boys were in the school, with me, and after they'd been about the forth form, they
 
went off for some - I don't know where they went, to different schools you know, not Llanduff, Llandovey was a favourite one, and boys of that class would go you see. They'd be in the school 'til they were about - a few years, say five or six, and then th
ey've be - go off you see, to these other schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh no. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not very much. Not - not in that way
, not - not that you could recognize, only sports I mean those of you who ; no it was mostly the age groups, that's the only difference that you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you go on to another school after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well no. Went to college. Oh well then we had - they had a teachers training - cent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5532069\charrsid2756420 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 e in Cardiff. For pupil teachers, used to call 'em. See I went there for a year.
