\insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 school, did you continue to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Although I was at college I lived at home - actually I left college you see. Until the war came -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You had to live in college did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, no, I lived here. Yes, always at home all the time you see. I - always lived home. Until I wa
s in the - until I went to Canada you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What did they think of you going to Canada?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 My father didn't like it very much. But - all right. That was a 
new idea rather with them - with us and - he didn't seem to - well he didn't object or anything like that you see but I think he felt it a bit, he - he wasn't quite - he was - I don't think he was like adventurous in that way you see. I didn't mind, I was
 on top of the world as far as going you see, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well she was very quiet, she never says anything much about anything in that way you see, she never said yes or no you see. She never seemed to say - express any opinions like that. No. No, she used to - took - take things as they came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, well they didn't care very much. My - my - of course my old - elder brother, he had been - he had been to South Africa, and he came ba
ck at the beginning of the war you see. So he was back for - for that, otherwise he'd - he'd had a couple of years in South Africa you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 That had paved the way rather then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Paved the way, oh yes, yes. Oh yes, well it wasn't very strange, peop
le were doing it all the time and all that. My father was a little - more of a - local sort of a man you see, had always been - he'd been and brought up in Cardiff you see, and all that. But - I don't - he never said - after all, I was back within twelve 
months. IT'S ONLY a year you see, was only a year, yes, oh yes, only a year. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No. Oh no, no, I kept on the same. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not 
to Sunday school, I - oh I did, yes, 'cos it was more of a lecture there, it was big, it was rather in a big way there you see. Didn't seem to be quite like Sunday school but it was, oh I used to go regularly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Not active - of course, not what you'd call - you'd call - you couldn't - not until I came back home here you see. Then I did. That wasn't 'til about twenty - twenty-two. Yes, well I can tell you I came and gradually got into things round here then
. But not - tremendously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What would your views be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh it was the Liberal, the old Liberal party, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Why did you think like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh was brought up to it more like that. Agree with it roughly up to a point you see. General
ly. Oh yes, and non-conformist and all that was all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you vote in an election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh - well now - before 1919? Oh no, I suppose in the Army, I don't know. Of course we had - had the university vote you see. In 1914. I've got an idea
 - I - I must have got a postal vote. I can't remember - at all, 'cos always - my father was always interested in politics you see and I was up to - in that way you see. Quietly. Yes, yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you remember what you voted for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well yes, old Liberal party all - we always had - always had a Liberal candidate then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever feel under any pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 No, not in those - no, no more than that - was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You said that the family were Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh we were - we were brought up that way, you had general ideas you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Were you actually a member of the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Eventually - in - about 1922 - on my own you see. See the war came in and give up everything you see. And I suppose w
e had a postal - I've got some idea - yes, of course, no, no, that was after the war wasn't it, 19 - don't suppose I could have voted 'til about 1920. Because I wasn't home. And there wouldn't be elections you see. There was the 1919 after the - directly 
after the war, I'd rather - I - I must have had a vote then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well only in a local way, you know - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever take part in political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No. Well they never did anything, very - very funny here, it used to go dead here after elections see. Always disband. Well - well, as a rule they've got - they have got to disband for the election time, you see. And - and then they form up again you s
ee, reform - was merely a formal thing you see. But they never did anything, you couldn't - they complain here, the big people here at Whitchurch wanted to - election you see, so - so you couldn't get any - couldn't get a meeting of any kind you see. They
 
actually tried it by getting the Conservatives and Labour - there was a - bunch of young men coming up then, there was - Warren Evans, do you remember during - were you here then - Warren Evans was - Elfin David, and there was some young fellows from Card
i
ff, they were young lawyers and that you see, and they tried to work - work up here you see, and eventually they got a - a meeting - a couple of meetings by the Conservatives and the - and the Liberal amongst them, see had a united meeting, and then they 
c
ouldn't - it'd go dead, absolutely dead until election came you see. And work up from nothing. You - I've seen that process three or four times, I've been through it you see. It was a ridiculous business really. But that - that's - that's what happened ac
tually - you see
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 They're not very interested politically around here are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Not - not really, oh no. No, no. No, not at all, no. Because there was none of that protest that you get today. See, all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 What about your spare
 time then after you'd left school, how would you spend your spare time? Did you used to go walking and bicycling and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. Yes, yes. That's about all, and gardening. I took on the garden, my father was giving up gradually you see
. I remember one time - funniest thing - there was - we had a holly tree growing from the front, it's something like I've got round the side, well I had one - and it got up and was darkening the - the - actually darkening the room you see a bit, and that 
w
as right in front of his bedroom window there. And he said, oh I must get that down, cut it down. But he never did, he had all these meetings and things you see. So I remember one Saturday morning my brother was home, I said, lend me a hand and we'll get 
t
his down you see. So we got out a saw and got it down in a few minutes really. When he comes in from town, oh - I can't call my house my own. He was playing up he was. But that's the thing what we got for it you see. No, I took on - took on the gardening 
r
eally from that time and - always did it, he went to - built me a greenhouse really, when I settled in there, he - always going to do it, but he never got round to doing it you see, 'til I come to live - there were pieces of it cut out - all there in his 
w
orkshop, from the time - from before the war I expect. Years you see. Windows half made or - sections of it half made in glass, and he turned round, when I came home and that and I was there - and - and together see, he might give me - he was getting a bi
t - old for it, bit heavy for climbing about, between us we put up this greenhouse, see. And from then on of course every - about two years after that he - he died rather suddenly really. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 So you really spent most of your spare time gardening did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh yes, that - except as you say going off in summertime, going bathing, I used to like to go off and have - get a - you know, I'd cycle down to Penarth, I'd cycle down to West Bay - what do you call it, St Mary Wells Bay, that became fashionab
le, that time it had a lot there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not a lot. Not regular. Well weren't things round here. I - would go in town Saturdays to cinemas, regular you see, oh yes, from here.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you go with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well - I'd go mostly by myself in the latter years, you see after the war - everything had - all your friends had gone you see and - disappeared. I'd go with my brother something, but most - most - more often than not I'd go - very funny really, I was goi
n
g every Saturday regular see. And eventually one - one Saturday morning went down - go down Curtaiz, catch a bus - a tram there, take you into Queen Street you see from - from the barracks about they'd stop then, and - go down into Queen Street and - walk
 
up and look at the cinemas, and one Saturday - one Saturday I done - oh I've seen this before, the old wild west you see, another one, and I walked on up the other side, went and got the next tram and came home, and I - I never went just - only to the pic
t
ures business. It had to be - oh everybody saw some - special one you see. And there was one special, everybody had seen it or - what was it, the Ten Commandments and then there was - A birth of a Nation I think was the first of that type of thing and - t
h
ings like that you see, then right on the last I think it was - what's it - something about Song - Julie Andrews was in it, what do you call it? Those were the last ones you see and the wife wanted to see those. Sound of Music wasn't it? I think that's th
e last one, you see, that everybody talked about and this, that, we had to go and see it you see. Otherwise I never went to - just to go to the pictures. After that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 When you went out then in those days did you go on your own, who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh mostly on my own, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you make any new friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Not much. No. No. Not - not - not - no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you ever bring any friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Never did much, only - only the old boy that - boys that I knew as a boy oc
casionally, one or two. No, I - I never did much of this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did you have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
No. The only - only few from the chapel. There were the few years after I came after the war there was - like - those - from the chapel, us
ed to do that, and - we didn't - like - Christmas, I mean Christmas party - there was a - a vogue for kind of whist drives Small whist drives in the house, we did have that for a few years, few winters. After - just at that period you see. And that's all.
 They're all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You would go to those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Oh we'd run them, yes, run them in - in each others houses a bit you see. Over the Christmas, I remember one Christmas saying - I've been to twenty-two I think or something like that different outings in that
 way you see. In the other - of course that was about the height of it you see because that sort of thing dies off, and it's gone anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you be going with boys, boyfriends or girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Well we all mixed in the chapel lot you see, becau
se my sisters had three or four - they were - you know, in it you see. It was all a proper bunch of us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You'd go into each others homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Yes. I remember there was a lady - came to the chapel only a few months ago - that's right, she's be
en living in - she married a - McKinsey her name was then, and they went to - went to - Western from here, and she married - she married - she was in a bank, working in a bank, she married the manager eventually, of the bank in - in Western, and she was o
v
er here visiting a few weeks ago - months ago now, and she's remembering how we used to go off on cycle rides - when she was - you see, like the young people of the chapel you see. So I remembered - I - I'd forgot - I'd forgotten about - oh most of us - w
e'd go as far as - perhaps \{BLANK\} Major I think once or twice we did, just on the coast, you see, oh yes, we did once - oh yes, once or twice. I remember going about that - that's about the farthest you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh well, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Would you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 
Well - yes, you were never very - of course this nine o'clock supper business, that was the standard then you see. But we - we used to vary, used to - when yo
u gets - growing older you see. Well that's only when you're - quite young. The sort of thing that used to happen with me and I used to go off - and I was supposed to be back, of course tea at five o'clock, so I'd go off for a good long walk, I - goodness
 knows when I'd come back, all depends if I got lost or not. More or less you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11162986 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 You were a big walker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959078 RL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7538088\charrsid2756420 Oh yes. That way, and then - and when I was a - when I was down - Suffolk I used to do a lot of it then. More than you see after the wa
r and all that like. Again - and of course get - I would get lost there, I wouldn't know where I was you see. I'd go over an hour or two late for tea. Because I was in lodgings then you see.
\par }}